    "288212998721955312007/07/31 18:10:46RivenI just did this quest for the first time on one of my alts. I did it as a shaman so I used water walking to get to the very southern point of Tanaris. I avoided the level 50 turtles for the most part (I did this at level 45) but it took some tricky dodging because they were all pathing around the mast I had to click on. I opened it up, went ghost wolf to a clear area so as not to pull aggro, and pulled 2 of the pirates nearby and killed them (it spawned five, but they split into two groups in a few moments). Dodging the turtles again I ran back and opened up the chest and ran for it after it went into my inventory. Aggro'ed a turtle while I was there but ran until it de-aggroed. I got lucky and got a blue pattern from the treasure for Mithril Shield Spike! Also got Cuergo's Gold (of course), a couple greys and a pair of green boots. Getting down to the location of the treasure was annoying, but it was worth it to get a blue prize inside! Just be careful not to die cause it's a looooong run back to your corpse.",
