    "4866175233101752332007/10/26 15:24:20Warlock82This quest is actually soloable as a Rogue - that's how I did it back in the day.  The key is to get to a position where you *only* aggro Mother Smolderweb (as you're coming up the first ramp, the very far right corner should work I think), then have her attack and poison you.  If you are lucky enough, you can do this before she kills you (evasion might help here, I assume you can't dodge the poison effect).  Pop a vanish, get to safety, then hearth the heck out of there.  (setting your hearthstone up near Burning Steppes helps)\
\
A Druid can also probably do this if they can hibernate her after they get poisoned. \
\
It's been a LONG time since I've done this (basically not long after the game came out), but I can't see how it wouldn't still be possible.",
    "48662031161133502007/01/12 03:14:19NimchipAlso make sure nobody cleanses you or anything of the like.. I did this quest and upon porting to IF, a paladin thought it might be helpful if he removed my poison. Needless to say, I failed the quest.",
    "4866177625201776252007/11/01 08:04:16novemberYes, it is still possible to solo the quest as a rogue this way. I just did. \
\
A good spot to aggro Mother Smolderweb and to hearth out afterwards was the far corner, I found.\
\
One word of warning, though: I died once because I simply didn't notice that she had already poisoned me.\
I had already come here to post a frustrated entry about how I had held out sooo long and still died unpoisoned before I thought to check my combat log, where - right before I used blinding powder, so I must have been fairly down but still in the first half of the fight - it actually said \"You are afflicted by Mother's Milk\". So there it was, and I hadn't seen it. - Quite apart from the fact that the poison shows as a bright green icon where all the poisons and spells you have on you are shown. Duh.\
\
Anyway, in the next fight, I left my combat log on and kept a constant eye on it. \
\
So, if you're as blind as me and tend to ignore your debuff icons, you might want to go into this fight with your combat log open, as well.\
