And eventually the Battle of Darrowshire:\
http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=5721",
    "51687779530777952007/05/04 15:46:21LauralynI suggest at least a small group to do this quest and the ones that follow it for anyone below lvl 60. This quest is a chain with a followup. Once you complete \"Heroes of Darrowshire\" and \"Villains of Darrowshire\" you are then able to get a new quest from Carlin Redpath called \"Marauders of Darrowshire\". Finish that and you can get \"Battle of Darrowshire.\" Then \"Hidden Treasures\" is last and gives you a choice of these quest rewards: \
[Ring of Protection] or [Archlight Talisman] or [Magebane Scion]\
\
Good luck to you and I hope all goes well!\
Also if this was helpful to you please rate it up.  TY!\
\
~Tessalyn, Dragonblight server",
    "5168132539101325392007/08/05 09:02:15SushilashThere were two Paladins in the first little room, one in the second room and two in the room where the Libram is. I ran inside to the end of the room, died, ran back and ressed. I scorched one of the Paladins so i would aggro, i froze them got the book and ran out.",
    "5168185340101853402007/11/15 19:12:18McWhirterThis quest now gives 8450xp in patch 2.3",
    "51685524470552442007/03/22 07:20:45tntiseverywereIf you are lucky in the same room with Davil's Libram you will find Scarlet Judge... a rare spawn :)",
    "516870333070332006/12/06 06:01:47dsrboThe libram is in the house looking like the Southshore Inn, first floor, inner room, on a table. It glows.\
\
You can avoid fighting into hearthglen, if you have done the quest \"Scarlet Subterfuge\" before. Just talk to \"Myranda the Hag\", get the Scarlet Illusion buff and walk into Harthglen to get the book.\
\
When you loot the book, the Scarlet Illusion will get removed. Since I play priest, I just caster Power Word: Shield, Fear, and run off after looting the book.",
    "5168116849301168492007/07/07 07:07:35shadedarkanThis quest is of moderate difficulty to do without dieing. I did this as a level 60 warlock.\
\
The shield is the easiest, but watch out for aggro from the haunts standing around the grain silos (If you did the time rift quest in Andorahl for the bronze dragonflight you will recognize these structures).\
\
The book is in the main (large room) of the building at 42,19 on the table just as you enter the room. The building has a large clock tower. I had to kill 7 mobs to get the book safely.  I pulled the two guards in front of the gate to Hearthglen down the road a ways and feared them unto death. All of the mobs can self heal so this makes the quest difficult especially if fighting two at a time. I was able to go left upon entering the town and stayed close to the left wall and bypassed the mob just to the right. \
\
Follow the left path up around up the hill and the building is straight ahead on the left, next to the ballista missile sqaud. There is a 61 elite that walks up and down the road so watch out for him. I pulled the mob standing to the left of the stairs in front of the clocktower building down the road and killed him. The mob standing on the right of the stairs I pulled behind the building where I could fear him so he couldn't heal. This makes killing the mobs very easy. Next, I had a double pull from just inside the entrance, again, around the back of the building so I could fear. They died, but took longer. The little room just before the main room has one mob so I pulled him around back a took care of business. I then had my void attack the two guards in the main room grabbed the book and ran. I didn't use sacrifice since when you get so far away from your void he disappears you leave combat immediately and you get your soul shard back. Right before the entrance to Hearthglen I summoned my horse and fled cackling all the way.",
    "516852405330524052007/03/17 00:32:10DorthThe Shield is at 64,57\
Outsite the Barn\
\
The Libram is at 42,18\
Inside the Town House\
\
Items are in WESTERN PLAGUELANDS",
    "5168210116111783562007/12/30 21:41:57darth603There's an alliance version of the same quest, but neither is really needed anymore.",
    "5168163439211625812007/10/05 17:57:54temporarilyhumanWell, if you're a rogue in a hurry, like me:\
\
1) Ride your mount past mobs at gate. They leash.\
\
2) Stealth into the town hall building (west edge of town). \
\
3) If you run into the rare mob inside, he paths up onto the stage alone. Kill or distract him there.\
\
4) Sap one of the two paladins by the book and Blind the other.\
\
5) Take the book, Vanish, and get back to the lonely rogue-ettes waiting in Ravenholdt, amirite?",
    "516817752611524052007/11/01 01:23:52zuikoIt's a city hall, not a town house. And the coordinates are not correct. I forgot to get the correct coordinates, but these are near the entrance and the city hall is in the back of the town. It's the same city hall model you see used just about everywhere so it is pretty recognizable. \
\
