    "7364930061154812007/03/10 19:38:33thaenI managed to solo these as a 45 blood elf protection-spec Paladin. Mogh is by far the hardest. Some advice for him:\
\
There are two guards. One is a minion, the other is not. There is a fourth mob that patrols between Mogh and a spot a little ways away. He is not linked, so you should wait until he is at his away-from-Mogh spot before pulling. \
\
The minion heals, so you should kill him first. He dies fast, but you'll have to interrupt and DPS relatively fast. Hammer of Wrath is great for this.\
\
Be prepared to bubble and heal. Mogh himself casts shadowbolts that hit for around 250, but he has a limited amount of mana, so if you survive through his mana bar, he hits like a mage. Seal of Light and Judgement of Light will keep you alive while killing him and the other headhunter.",
    "73615481150154812006/12/14 10:49:48ravenarkThe items drop off the following mobs:\
\
Grel'borg the Miser in Alterac Mountains. (Nb Coordinates, Patrolling Mob of Alterac)\
Grel'borg moves from the Town Hall to the Castle.    He starts in the Town hall, but I found him  just inside the castle door off to the left.  \
\
Mogh the Undying  - Stranglethorn Vale - (48,44)\
This mob is located at 48,44 with two other mobs as bodyguards.  He's easy to kill with two people attacking, so I recommend you take someone else along because it's nearly impossible alone.  He has a regeneration of his health which makes him so hard, so remember to bring heavy DPS.\
\
Dagon the Ravenous -  Dustwallow Marsh -  (59, 9)\
Roam around the island searching for a Mirefin Oracle on the outer edge,  You need to kill Mirefin Oracles to get the piece of Kelp required to summon Dagon the Ravenous.  When you place the Kelp inside an altar at the coordinates, Dagon comes out of the water and onto the beach.  He's rather easy to kill though, but I recommend you bring a friend with you.",
