    "452118106241217352007/11/08 14:37:01XsearRaging\
\
Start with this mob. Go to 58, 34. Search this area, both sides and you should at least find about 4 mobs. Use your mount, its a freakin \"pile\" mount-ain.\
Then slide down the cliffs, be careful with the fall dmg which suprise you sometime ;) If you have a \"map\", you should see two mountains with a cave in like just ahead of you, you should discover it somewhat after sliding down the hill. First go to the cave (Moon Horror Den, 60,29) and you SHOULD find 3 of them there. I count these as known spawns, its a good start of. Then, mount your mount and travel the mountains that lies around the cave. Start from the edge of one of them and ride the whole way through to the other side. You should find about 5 mobs.\
Then youl just continue searchin around, waiting for spawns etc.\
\
\
Ragged\
\
Start from 30,35 and go straight west. There are many Ragged Owls on the way, aswell as other mobs. When you get to a lake (37,35) with nice hot springs, you should find 3 of the Ragged just a little south of this lake. You should be able to see the lake, its just about 20 yards away. You can now, if you want to, go and search the southern parts, about 29, 36 if you want to and explore the mountains there (I didn't do that, there might be more there). Else. simply wait for respawns.\
\
The Raging will use an Enrage style of attack, i didn't read it with my detect magic yet but still, you know its Enrage so keep the healthbar on check.\
Else, theyl use some rend attack that does dmg over time.\
\
The Ragged doesn't Enrage, but they might cast a disease called \"Festering Rash\" (All attributes reduced by 22) which lasts for 30 mins. Nothing special though. Theyl aswell use a rend attack doing dmg over time.",
