    "512115952npcDonova Snowden9298npcDonova Snowden92986400Everlook250150832508435085450865508765121",
    "5121175000201750002007/10/26 04:18:35LxFxSolo'd as a lvl 55 Balance Druid. Did this in 2 parts\
1) take out the adds while rooting the elite, afterwards ran away to get out of combat\
2) return for the elite chief with my Treants and my yeti\
 - kept him rooted again\
 - faerie fire to lower his armor to get max physical dmg out of him (treants + yeti)\
 - kept dots up (moonfire + insect swarm)\
 - when nothing to do, just kept nuking him with starfire\
 - no pots/innervate needed\
\
Ok had some occasional \"misses\" because of the level difference, but otherwise a very easy elite in my opinion.... Good luck to you all\
\
PS: Dont forget the book, i did, even after reading this page... ;-)",
    "5121116851501168512007/07/07 07:18:14WoefulPeanutIf you do Are We There, Yeti? (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=5163) first, you can use the mechanical yeti reward to aggro one or both of the adds. By doing this I soloed it quite easy as a 58 druid.",
    "5121180635201806352007/11/07 15:34:17jbwestEasily doable as a 56 feral druid.  Dire Bear (about 7300 armor), wail on the chief, frenzied regen at about 1/3 health, keep wailing (mangle/swipe), at about 1/3 health again, pop out, barkskin, healing touch->regrowth->rejuv, back to dire bear.  Chief will die and you'll be at full health to take on the other two (who will be at about 3/4).  \
\
Unluckily for me, the runners showed up with the other 2 at half health.  So, i looted the chief real quick, travel form, and ran away.",
    "5121185917611840772007/11/16 17:46:15diagAnd he has 1 guard instead of 2 : )",
    "5121169340301693402007/10/15 20:05:23Discombobulator57 afflic lock, this was a joke. Just make sure you clear the top shelf of mobs (right before the chief's cave) out completely, and make your pull shortly after. I opened up with a full dot cycle on the chief, let him and his two buds aggro to me, dropped instant Howl of Terror, sent the feldoggy to hold the shaman's aggro, chain-feared the Chief as I kept the dots up and drain tanked the third add's damage (from the Chief's health, that is). Chief dropped, I moved in on the shaman, dropped him, moved in on \
\
Never even had to use a healthstone or pot. Of course results may vary with your luck of resists. Chief has relatively low HP for a 59 elite, so just make sure you open up and tear him down fast, even if it means breaking the adds' aggro.",
    "5121128122401281222007/07/28 06:46:57HunterOfWhelpsSoloed as a 55 priest.\
\
MC'ed one of the non-elites and let it get beaten to death by the other two - ran out, rinsed, and repeated for the second add.\
\
Fight against elite is tough, treat him as so and you'll beat him down easy enough",
    "512111178721982892007/06/27 10:15:53InquirySoloed this as a 55 Ret Paladin. Took me couple tried to get it right. I pulled the Ursa and ran back until the other 2 deaggrod. Killed the Ursa, then went back and killed the Shaman. His guards do not respawn right away. When I faced the High Chief I used the Mechanical Yeti to aid me. I dps him while occasionally healing my Yeti. In all I only had to use 1 mana pot. No other cooldowns except bubble at the end.\
\
Also..try to do this quest with \"Winterfall Activity\".",
    "5121190367301903672007/11/24 10:20:45AllgardI received 11600 XP doing this as a lvl 60 mage.",
    "5121148645601486452007/09/03 13:47:28ccgdoodCo-ords are 69,38. The boss also gives nice Timbermaw rep.",
    "5121184077601840772007/11/14 07:44:02AlexeiDHigh Chief is non-elite as of patch 2.3.0 (and many other mini-bosses are), isn't a problem to solo now.",
    "5121160658201606582007/09/30 03:05:49SpinDrJrWas able to solo this as a 57 shadow priest. I quickly cast mind soothe on all the mobs then mind controlled the elite. I was easily able to burn one of the adds down and start on the second before mind control broke, by that time the adds had hurt the elite pretty bad too. I bubbled, dotted elite, physic screamed them both away, and finished off the elite, then finished off the last add.\
\
I highly recommend that you mind control the ELITE as the adds will do most of the dps for you on the elite.",
    "5121911710091172006/12/07 17:43:24synthetixThe Chief is in the cave above the winterfall village (NOT the Yeti cave!). Respawn seems to be about 5-10min.\
He is surrounded by 2 non elites and the Chief by himself is a very easy elite, you just need some way to CC the adds.\
\
Also before you start the fight make sure the winterfall runners are not going to jump you from behind since they do end their run here.",
    "512110500161493912007/06/15 15:44:01WarluckyThe book is http://www.wowhead.com/?item=12842",
    "5121120836211171262007/07/15 02:35:38todd1I managed it as a 56 shadow priest (although I didn't use shadowform for the fight). Kill an add, get out of combat. Kill the second add, and get out of combat. All that's left is the elite. Just kill him like you would any other mob, but remember to fear when it's up. I had to use one superior mana potion and ended up using Flash Heal on myself twice.\
\
On my first attempt, I killed one add and ran. Then I used Mind Soothe on the two remaining mobs so I could get close enough to Mind Control the elite. That seemed to work fairly well, but Mind Control broke early and by the time I killed off the non-elite add, I didn't have enough mana to kill the elite and I died.",
    "512149391130493912007/03/11 00:53:48ItsallmuscleAfter you kill him he drops a book that will give you another quest that you turn in to Donovan (same person that gave you this quest). So be sure to loot him before you run away from the mob",
