    "648100482201004822007/06/08 01:20:51davsfcI done this quest as a lvl 43 prot (AoE) pally, it took two attempts. The first time the chicken died when i bubbled against the Mage and the 2 assassins because he pulled all the agro. I healed and ruined their day (but really they had already ruined mine!). Anyway, next time i got through with no problems. Tactics: I killed the scopids pally AoE style (BoSanc, Ret Aura, SoLight, holy shield). I consecrated to pull any agro off the chicken. (remember we don’t want him to die!) This was the toughest fight by far. I think i even used Lay on hands after some wolf joined in. I killed everything slowly from then on so that my health and mana kept going up, BoWis, SoL does it for pallys. I changed to Prot Aura too for the chicken! Keep an eye on the chicken’s health; take as much beating as you need to so that he has time to heal. You can always take a potion or bandage. (I couldn’t heal the chicken). I switched to Shadow res Aura before i got to the mage and Co. Killed mage first, pulled the agro from the chicken with consecration. Then went back to pally AoE again to finish off the assassins. They dual wield so happy days. (The chicken doesn’t take well to dual wielders though!) He died quick the first time! There was no other trouble. Sorry this is really only a pally guide....\
The longest part of this was finding the chicken! Which got me killed once but the second time i pulled a lvl 50 basilisk and half way through that i pulled another lvl 50 giant bug that dropped critters. (they died on my BoSanc though! lol) I survived it though but the fight took so long the basilisk had disappeared (and i couldn’t loot it!) by the time I had finished off the bug! (really what happens is that you try and keep your health up (Jol Sol) while holy damage (ret Aura, BoSanc, Shield spike) slowly kills them!)",
    "648119473201194732007/07/12 10:06:07NiffesEasy soloed by a 48 Shadowpriest. Just fear the ambushes and keep Shadow Word Pain on all mobs in the ambushes",
    "648205518111906632007/12/22 10:59:24CelwindiaSolo'd this the other day as a 48 SPriest.  Instead of fearing ambushers for the escort quests, I usually try to find a different way.  \
\
The first group I thought would be like the previous groups I ran into, and come from a distance, so I mounted and scorpions spawn in a circle surrounding the chicken, and immediately start attacking.  Throw dots, attacks, or get some kind of aggro from all of them, and just focus on the one he's focused on.  For reference, I found my chicken was able to stay alive for at least 25 or so seconds, easily with one scorpion and poison on him.  If you're a lower level, don't attack the mob that the chicken is focused on, take 2 off of him, and take the 3rd when you've finished one, the chicken should survive comfortably, as should you.\
\
The chicken ran past or into several mobs on the way,  before, after, and in between ambushes.  I didn't find these happening too terribly often, every 20-30 seconds of dead time.  I just join him in the fight, these are typically single mobs, I got occasional doubles.\
\
The second group does approach from a distance, so I was able to mount and kite them, just running through, and then past the group.  The mage was only able to cast on me once, and the melees got 2 attacks per?  After seeing this was quite possible, I dropped mount and engaged.  I threw dots on the assassin's, and then just focused on the mage, they dropped with no fuss.\
\
A few helpful things to remember, I wasn't able to buff or heal the chicken whatsoever, but within 10 seconds of leaving combat, that cheesy NPC regen kicks in, and he's full in 2 ticks.  If his health is really low, and he's walking directly towards a mob, simply go to the side of the path, and pull the mob yourself, keeping it out of the chicken's aggro range, he'll walk right past, and you can finish the mob yourself.  Also, bandages are extremely helpful, just remember that they can be interrupted easily, wait until the scorpids' poison wears off before you bandage, or you'll have a minute to wait to try again =P  Hope this helps.  5450 XP\
\
Edited for typos and the like.",
