    "276682222082222006/12/07 03:42:32enasimaSoloed this as a 46 mage actually. The main problem is getting from the cave to the road.. generally a bear or ape will agro as the three yeti that spawn about 30m from the road attack, which can make for a very tough fight. The other spawns(gorillas followed by some gnolls) are easier to deal with ~ not much worry of outside agro either.",
    "27666393320639332007/04/08 15:16:37JohnJSalI'm going to post this message on all three of these \"Find\" quests, just in case someone doesn't see it on one of the other two.\
\
If you plan to do these quests in a group (which is very helpful, as any escort quest) everyone must first have completed the \"Find\" part of the quest, which means you have to find the chicken, choose \"Complete\" and then be *offered* the next part of the quest, which is the actual escort part. But do not accept this part until everyone has done the \"Find\" part, otherwise it won't be offered to them as escort quests normally are, because technically you are not on the same stage of the quest yet.\
\
So just complete the \"Find\" part, then when the next part is offered, decline it until everyone is ready to accept it.",
    "2766144191111245032007/08/26 05:07:21MandieLet the chicken tank one or two. If you tank all of them he'll go ahead alone and you'll fail the quest.",
    "2766124503401245032007/07/21 12:10:14Cads1. Clear through the yeti cave, accept the escort quest.\
2. Escort the chicken until he is ambushed by yetis. Abandon the quest and let him die.\
3. Run back through the cave quickly before respawns and accept again.\
4. You may now bypass the yeti ambush; the chicken will run straight to the road and the yetis that did not despawn will ignore him.\
5. You'll be ambushed by 3 apes on the road, no other mobs will interfere. Once they're dead, restore health and mana asap.\
6. Shortly after the bridge you'll be ambushed by 4 gnolls. The mystic can and will heal.\
7. It helps to let the chicken tank 1 or 2 of them.",
