    "448422187022182006/10/24 13:50:06jasonThis is actually quite useful for a paladin.  Consider what the +8 Int does for us.  First, +8 Int.  Assuming at 60 the paladin formula for spell crit is:\
\
[INT/29.5?]%\
\
This gives us .27% crit chance for 8 Int.\
\
Now, also assume that paladins have Divine Intellect, and Blessing of Kings, that increases the 8 int to about 9.6 (or 9.68, however, they do the math) int.  Assuming they round up, that's 10 int.\
\
Compare this to the ZG enchant, which give us 10 Stamina, 24 healing, and 7 defense.  Assuming at this point that defense is all but useless for a current end-game raiding paladin, it comes down to +healing and stamina and more mana and spell crit.\
\
With two enchants, you have the following totals:\
\
ZG: 48 +healing, 200 health\
LIbram: 20 Int (assuming BoK and DI talent), which gives us .54% spell crit, ~300 mana\
\
Considering the limited number of ZG enchants you can get these days, +8 int doesn't look that bad.",
    "4484170335111445102007/10/17 10:05:46PersenConsidering the prices, the 20 extra HP a Constitution gives might not be worth it... This one you should be able to get pretty cheaply.",
    "4484161608211445102007/10/01 23:13:23BlueScrnActually [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=11733]Libram of Constitution[/url] (+100 HP) is better and every decent twink should have that or 8 agility from this libram.",
    "4484207438102074382007/12/26 06:46:19DeddeIs these ones avable for twinks through the trade window, just like the 100+ hp one? Just want to be sure.",
    "4484180575111445102007/11/07 13:44:18TenjouFor demo locks, Voracity (+8 STA) is a much better choice than Constitution (+100 HP).\
\
5/5 Demonic Embrace will raise your STA gained by 15% -- 9.2 STA. That will be equal to 90 or 100 HP, depending on the rounding with the rest of your gear.\
\
In addition to the 90/100 HP:\
\
+ Your pet's STA will be based off of a percentage of your STA, not your HP.\
+ The percentage of +9.2 STA going toward your pet will be increased by another 15% with 3/3 Fel Stamina -- a percentage of +10.58 STA.\
+ And then a percentage of this increase in STA will be added by 3/3 Demonic Knowledge as an increase to spell damage based off of 15% of your pet's total STA and INT.\
\
+8 STA is vastly superior to +100 HP. Equivalent HP gain, more HP for your pet, and more +spell dmg for you.\
\
And if you're ever buffed with Blessing of Kings, that's an extra 10% STA right there. +100 HP will always be only +100 HP.",
