    "7861381012038102006/11/17 14:49:34OrmrissThe priestess is at the very top of the city.  It's a good idea to go get the hammer for ZF from the Altar of Zul before doing this quest.  The priestess patrols around the altar needed to enchant the ZF mallet.  In addition, Elder Torntusk is on the altar.  Finishing the next part of his quest requires going into the cave behind the altar, which is where you can finish killing all the guards needed to complete this quest.  You can kill several birds with one stone if you play it right.\
\
Fighting the priestess, I was able to do it with a 54 shaman and 49 shaman.  She likes to polymorph you, and the spell won't break from damage nor will it cause you to regenerate.  She also uses Shadow Word: Pain, so be ready with some heals.  Be sure to take out the nearby guards and dogs before pulling her, she will run once her health gets low.",
    "7861191247211840662007/11/25 21:29:38zuikoIf you put out enough DPS she wont even have a chance to get any spells off. My mage soloed her twice in a row... took less than 5 seconds for her to go down. She casts SW:Pain, then tries to get off a heal, then dies. Doesn't even have a chance to hex if you dps enough.",
    "7861184066601840662007/11/14 07:26:41mbroooksIn 2.3, this quest is now to kill 10 guards and Hexx, and the guards aren't elite any more, so this isn't classified as a group quest.  Both rewards are top notch.",
    "7861797742138102007/05/08 11:43:20deadaloneIf you are a warlock or have a warlock in group.. just have your felhunter out and devour the hex debuff thing. That is, if you do not have a priest / pally to dispel.",
    "7861188801311840662007/11/21 09:50:42ZulazingYou will still need a group to kill her because of the poly, but 2 should be enough. I tried to solo her on my 48 prot pally, and a 51 mob would normally be no problem, but you only have a second or so between polys. I bubbled out of the first one but was immediately poly'ed again. She doesn't hit that hard, on plate at least, but she still outpaced my reflective damage. Her DoT's and her melee will not break the poly, it has to wear off or be dispelled.",
    "7861193682211840662007/11/30 00:38:26catspats31In addition, this quest now gives 8800 XP as of patch 2.3",
    "7861201084111840662007/12/14 09:12:51tylerphilcoX2. I soloed with a 50 warrior and used pummel which stops her cast and prevents it for another 4 seconds. That 4 seconds was all I needed.",
    "7861206837102068372007/12/24 22:14:13GoldvingSolo'd as a poorly geared 48 Frost Mage.  She likes to chain Hex you and heal herself which is annoying.  Had to blow Cold Snap and two Ice Blocks (to get out of Hex to counterspell her heals) to kill her.",
