    "5846464610646462007/04/09 21:29:55PirotessaBoth coords were right for me. 23.7 for Gan'Zulah 23.9 for Nezzliok.\
\
Didn't have a problem as a 40 Paladin. Swam up to Gan'Zulah and only pulled him and one Witch Doctor.  Nezz was a bit harder, 4 mobs plus him. Managed to do it though.",
    "584207840202078402007/12/26 21:29:06AeriTracking- \
1. Gan' zulah - Strangelthorn Vale - [23.46, 8.14] / [23, 8]\
2. Nezzliok - Stranglethorn Vale - [23.46, 9.47] / [23, 9]\
3. Secret Path - Stranglethorn Vale - [26.32, 8.07] / [26, 8]\
\
Once you recieve the quest head north to the river that meets Nessingwary's Camp, Head west along the lake front until the hills south open up again. Head a little west into the hills here bordering the camp and find the spot where the wall and hills meet(3.). Runn along the wall untill you reach the higher Pool of water. Gan'zulah(1.) can be pulled solo but it's tough you will usually get one add. He is on a random spawn rate, can be 5 minutes can be 45 i've seen both. Nezzliok will always pull with the shammy beside him, again very easy fight.\
\
You can fight you way out, which is easy for most Melee, but us casters would look too running or hearthing. If you drop just west of the two quest mobs you can run past opposing force fairly easily, and then run the shore line back to Grom. Or just use the same path to get out as you got in, near the eastern edge of the upper pool you can hop back onto the ladge with ease.\
\
Happy Hunting and safe travels!\
Aeri - Kargath",
