    "7003168851401688512007/10/15 03:54:59ReeseRuizSo you get the quest from a lil goblin near the coast. Up and down that same coast are Wave Striders you can kill that will drop the Miniaturization Residue. I started doing this .... until i realized the other quests i had.\
\
If you go to 41, 21 in the Twin colossals, there are Giants up there you can zap and kill. They drop Metallic Fragments as well as the Miniaturization Residue. AND if you have the Muisek quests, you can get the Mountain Giant Muisek from them as well.\
\
THREE quests done in one area.\
PLEASE go up to 41,21 and dont waste yer time on the shore.\
\
Get the water elemental cores later... most of those you can get without even going in the water. This saves you water breathing potions, or recasting the water spell for locks.",
    "70037451311695452007/04/28 16:40:06GradosThe Zapper makes the giants go from elite status to normal mob status - just pick any giant - so it IS worth it, unless you've been trying to kill them without using the Zapper.",
    "70035775061134942007/03/26 21:07:37MaxtroJust to make this clear. Zorbin's Ultra-Shrinker from Zapped Giants does work on Land Walkers and Ciff Giants. When you kill the non-elite version you can get the Mountain Giant Muisek and Miniaturization Residue. However the Sea Giants next to the quest giver for Zapped Giants do not give Mountain Giant Muisek.\
\
Get Zapped Giants when you are on Mountain Giant Muisek and go after the Mountain Giants. You can do both quests at the same time.",
    "7003112560201125602007/06/28 22:39:24todd1It seems like any giant in Feralas works. As stated above, Horde can do Mountain Giant Muisek (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=3127) at the same time as this quest.\
\
The zapper does not trigger the global cooldown, which I found very helpful as a caster. It does have a 30 second cooldown, though, and it took about 20 seconds on average to kill a zapped giant as a level 50 shadow priest.\
\
The zapper disappears after 2 hours. If you started the quest, you have to abandon it and get it again. When you abandon the quest, any Miniaturization Residue you collected disappears.",
