    "50562011391132932007/12/14 11:48:09melwilthat is not correct, the procedure is the same for summoning and killing Shy-Rotam.\
\
However, neither Shy-Rotam or Siam Rotam are elite, they are regular mobs and easily soloed by any class now. It does seem like you might be able to kill Shy-Rotam fast enough to avoid her calling her mate, Siam Rotam spawned at 8% when I just did the quest.",
    "50561821070182102006/12/28 01:10:32OrmrissTried this with two shamans, me with a 60 restoration-spec shaman and my brother with a 59 elemental-spec.  We did ok starting off, though we did pull an add thanks to Shy-Rotam's fear.  It seemed like she used that every 15 seconds :)  Anyways, once she hits about 50% health, she summons her mate, also a level 60 elite.  This is where we wiped.\
\
I scoured the web for strategies, and read a suggestion that said hunters could start the fight, then kite her back to Everlook and have the guards there help kill her.  Taking that into account, we tried again.  This time, I tried kiting her with Frost Shock.  It was incredibly successful.\
\
Frost Shock slows the target for eight seconds, but only has a cooldown of six seconds.  What I did was cast Frost Shock to start off the fight, then ran towards the road.  If you use this strategy, note that you'll want to clear the frostsabers from the road beforehand.  I simply ran down the road, turning to cast Frost Shock whenever it's cooldown finished.  It's worth noting that at this point, I had about 5400 max mana, as well as the Elemental talents that increase Shock damage and decrease Shock mana cost.  Even with all that I still had to use a superior mana potion a ways down the road.  I was able to stay way ahead of Shy-Rotam, and well out of range of her fear.  Not only that, but once she got down to 50% health, she called for her mate, who did not appear.  My guess is that he spawns back at Shy-Rotam Rock.  I was so far off that he either never caught up or did not give chase.  Regardless, he was not a factor, and once Shy-Rotam got to around 10%, I dropped a Tremor Totem (to break Fear) and closed to finish the fight with melee and Earth Shock.\
\
My brother only used one Frost Shock, and that was at my suggestion, as a way for me to save a little mana on the road.  There was also a level 57 Alliance hunter who saw us and fired on Shy-Rotam a few times, but his damage was fairly small, mainly Concussive Shot (I assume he was trying to avoid pulling aggro).  After killing her, I still had about 800 mana and about 70% health.  The removal of her mate was the dealmaker here, so I recommend kiting her down the road if you can.",
