    "11454164558311637602007/10/08 02:20:02BrmonkeyNote: if you still have this quest (you cannot get it anymore) but have not completed it, you STILL can! The NPC you turn this quest into is in the grim guzzler and he will give you the follow up.\
\
So if you've got this quest consider yourself lucky!",
    "114541634061101634062007/10/05 16:45:24SilentviperThis quest can be started hourly, when the Dark Iron Invasion pops up again at xx:30. You have to find Coren Direbrew in Blackrock Depths. This guy is a bit hard to find if you don't know where to start looking for him, so i made a little walkthrough.\
\
First of all you got to have the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=11000]Shadowforge Key[/url], because you will need it for a few doors and a lever further along the way.\
As soon as you come through the BRD portal take a left but don't go to the Dark Iron Highway. Instead turn right and open the small door, immedately taking a left to open another door.\
In here there's a lever you need to pull for the bridge to lower up ahead.\
Once you've clicked the lever head up the ramp and cross the now available bridge.\
Work your way past a few groups of mobs at the other end of the bridge and you should pass [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=9033]General Angerforge[/url]. Head into the room adjacent to the general's room and then don't go straight ahead to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=8983]Golem Lord Argelmach[/url], but instead turn right past the room with the mechanicals and head through the passage there.\
Once you're in the Grim Guzzer you should see Coren walking up and down the room, but as soon as you approach him he runs away into the nearby hall. He hides near the Thorium Brotherhood questgiver so that's where you can complete the quest and receive your [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=34140]Dark Iron Tankard[/url], which gets you \"completely smashed\" instantly.\
\
Hope this helps you guys find him too.",
    "11454163618101636182007/10/06 06:39:00LieandraYou should note that getting to the Grim Guzzler is nothing new as a very good dagger drops from within. The [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=12791]Barman Shanker[/url] drops from [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=9499]Plugger Spazzring[/url] in the Grim Guzzler. As a result, there are a lot of [url=http://www.worldofroguecraft.com/shanker.html]guide[/url]s to getting inside of the Grim Guzzler.\
\
As a rogue, you can solo this particular quest as early as lvl ~50-52 as you need a minimum of 250 LockPicking for the 2 gates, the 1 door, and the 1 Gear. The gear will take some really good timing, but if you are a good enough rogue (know how to play your class), it will not be a problem for you. \
\
Technique: The far left corner of the gear room has two dwarves. You need to Sap the one closest to the corner, and then position yourself just close enough to the Gear (when you can first use the LockPicking ability) and the second dwarf to avoid agro from the other dwarves on the right and the dwarves behind you (the ones near the entrance), while LockPicking. \
\
At that position, you Blind the second dwarf and click on the gear. The Sap time and Blind time will be enough for the Lockpicking time of the Gear. (You can fail lockpicking, so trying again from fresh Cool Downs may be needed.) You must be aware of the one Fire Elemental pat, and be sure to await his leave before beginning.\
\
A successful Lockpicking of the Gear at low levels will agro the other dwarves in the room. At this time Vanish and they should all reset. Then you may continue to the Grim Guzzler.  Failing will require you to wait for BOTH Cool Downs (Vanish and Blind).\
\
Also, note that if you are Stealthed and inside the Grim Guzzler (I was curious). When you near Coren Direbrew, he will still run and hide in the back room.",
