    "5341211670102116702008/01/02 15:09:07SgtownI just solod this quest as a 70 resto druid, it can be done easily by any class, especially stealthers.\
\
Through some trial and error, I found out you can be within about 5 yards of the mobs in this instance without aggroing.\
\
I could open all the Iron doors without aggroing the guards near them.\
\
The first deed: stand in the very corner behind the 2 guards and open it, no aggro.\
\
Stealth through the next few rooms. Second deed: stand in front of the Iron Door right next to the deed, as far as possible from the mobs next to it. As long as the pat is moving away, you have plenty of time to unstealth, open the deed, and restealth.\
\
Now you have to kill Rattlegore. Go down to the whelp room, drop into a hole, kill enough adds to clear to the boss. Adds have like 15k HP, boss has 30k. Loot the key, go back upstairs and through the other way (watch out for the disease cloud mobs).\
\
If you stand along the wall of the locked door, in between the pulls, you can just barely reach the door and unlock it and continue.\
\
3rd deed is cake compared to what you did before, just stealth when you enter Ras's room, walk over to the sparkles and loot.\
\
Go back to the student room, go the other way. When you get to the final area, go down the stairs and straight forward.\
\
4th deed: Watch out for the Unholy Aura of Alexi Barov, it will damage you if it doesn't resist, which is about once every 3 pulses. Approach along the wall so you don't aggro the Risen Warriors.\
\
If you stick as close to the wall as possible, inching closer until you can open the deed, you won't aggro. It will take a few tries because you have to resist 3 aura pulses in a row or it will interrupt it.\
\
Return the way you came until you're out of the aura, hearth and pat yourself on the back!",
    "5341160511016052006/10/08 02:10:11DralmikinsDeed to South Shore:  in the large room after you cross the bridge from the instance portal.  It's in a small corner next to a bookshelf on top of a desk.\
\
Deed to Tarren Mill: It's on a desk to the right corner of the room before Dragon whelps.\
\
Deed to Brill: In the room where Ras Frostwhisper, the lich is.\
Deed to Caer Darrow: In the room where Lord Alexi Barov is.   It is one of the Six r\
oom with mini bosses at the bottom side.",
    "5341211672112116702008/01/02 15:16:38SgtownSome tips:\
\
I used +stealth gear, but I don't know that it's really necessary.\
\
If you aren't in a position where you have to fight, take off all your durability gear (rings, trinkets, back, offhand, necklace can stay on) so if you mess up it doesn't cost you.\
\
As a resto druid, I found PVP gear to be the easiest way to fight. In my PVE gear the Risen Constructs hit me for like 700 each, and over 1000 when they enraged and crit. In PVP gear Rattlegore hit me for like 400.\
\
Just keep 1x Lifebloom (or 3x if you want, but I like the burst) and rejuv on yourself, and moonfire on the mob. Cast wrath when all those are already up. There will be lots of pushback, but it's better than nothing. Barkskin is best used on the risen constructs when they enrage, so you can cast really quick.\
\
Other than that, gl, and keep at it! The peasant caller and gnome trinket from ZA together are too good to pass up, especially if you spec boomkin and summon trees too. ;)",
    "534161672061672006/12/05 12:50:51FiranThe deeds are scattered around scholomance. The deed to South Shore is in the first room of the instance on a desk. The deed to taurren mill is on a table, right before the whelp room, to the right. The deed to brill is on a ledge next to Ras Frostwhisper, and the last deed (Caer Darrow) is behind Lord Alexi Barov. \
\
An important thing to note is that if your party has ever been a raid (even with only 5 people in it) you will not be able to loot the deeds. You do not have to do any extra clearing to get the deeds either, so this quest is easy to get done in a pug.",
