    "3801198414019842006/10/17 09:54:58gndnYou can only grab this quest if you are in ghost form (dead) or someone that already has it shares it with you. You can find Franclorn Forgewright outside the instance. He is actually in the center of the big lava pit as you start running down the chains to head to BRD. He will be standing on top of a tomb.",
    "3802205549102055492007/12/22 11:52:01Pigvomitit should be noted that the \"arena\" mentioned in the first comment is the Ring of the Law.\
the directions were confusing for me because i was looking for something marked as arena and never found it. being one of the many players that didn't come on til after BC i had never run any of the Blackrock Mountain dungeons.",
    "380216106540161062006/12/15 22:47:38mauriceHere's how you get to Fineous:\
\
1) Go into BRD (duh).\
\
2) Go straight, clear your way to the path directly in front of you- this is the path that runs almost perfectly east/west along the southern side of the Arena.\
\
3) Go into the Arena and do the event. This will make the spectators at the top of the Arena (you'll be there in a second) passive. \
\
4) Go out the arena exit, it's to your left as you walk into the arena. You'll find yourself in a room with some DI Dwarves and some fire elementals. \
\
5) On the right there will be stairs/a ramp leading up to the spectator area of the arena. Walk to the other side of the arena, DO NOT ATTACK THE SPECTATORS.\
\
6) At the other end of the arena go down the ramp. Going right will take you to the statue you turn Ironfel in at. Head left to get to Fineous after crossing through a few rooms first. He's in the room with the large stone golems and the non-elite dwarves. He pats up and down the ramp. \
\
7) After you kill him head back the way you came, go past the entrance to the arena and continue on to the statue that is just around the corner.",
