    "53426052npcAlexi Barov11022npcAlexi Barov1102283001534125342",
    "5342168711101687112007/10/14 22:46:191yc1Did it yesterday with my wife, frostmage and shadowpriest, both lvl57, using kiting strategy. I pulled him with frostbolt, then we waited for few more frostbolts so I could get aggro and I runned from him, occasionally using bolts to slow him down, while my wife dotted him. \
\
I used elemental twice and still ran oom, used pot and mana giving orb from mage' class quest. I believe he can be soloed at lvl63-65 as frostmage, you can kite him w/o problems with just spamming your latest rank of frostbolts(I still used few rank1 to keep distance). \
\
I kited him by the road to Andorhal and when we came to brige, I turned toward trees and ran back to Alliance' flypoint, he died on half way.\
\
While you kite him, beware, this guy reached me once and I got him for around 1.5k hp, to my luck he never had a chance to repeat it. \
\
Good luck with him.",
    "5342187673201876732007/11/19 13:26:01pufferfishAfter patch 2.3, he is still a Eilte, but he is surprisingly much weaker than before.(I gave up once before patch 2.3 when I was Lv60) solo him as a Lv63 warlock. He cannot even kill my felguard now :)",
    "5342103411201034112007/06/13 02:10:45HattenschwilCasters beware: This mob is immune to fear and hits for just over 2k, so if you have a party of 3 level 62s, a priest, a warlock and a warrior, you will find yourself struggling.",
    "5342138562601385622007/08/15 21:27:14LKolmirHe can be taken by two mages using the following strategy.\
\
First mage will gain aggro using a high DPS spell, such pyroblast or Arcane Missles. At the same time the second mage will hit him with frostbolt to slow him.\
The first mage will kite him with using fireblast each time it is available. The second mage will repeatedly hit him with frostbolt.\
If/When the second mage gains his aggro the two mages swap roles. The second will kite with fireblast and the first will use frostbolt.\
\
This works very will if he is pulled over to the hills. The frostbolt mage can stand at the top of the hill and the fireblast mage can run around the bottom of the hill.\
\
I've done this with a 65 mage (fire spec) and a 62 mage (frost spec) and he went down very quickly and easily.",
    "5342138536801385362007/08/15 20:30:08TheOnyx[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=11023]Weldon Barov[/url] is immune to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=122]Frost Nova[/url], but not to the snare effect given by [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=11071]Frostbite[/url].",
    "534244385044382006/11/25 18:28:31tgardenRequires you to engage Weldon Barov at Chillwind Point. Easily taken in a 5man (have done him quite easily with just a warrior, hunter and priest), however you become PvP flagged and Weldon shouts for help so all Alliance in the area know you are there.\
\
Try him at odd hours and pull him up the road a little bit or over the hill - hopefully you will get him down before Alliance swarm all over you =)\
\
Gotta love the Home Alone references as well...",
    "5342169796101697962007/10/16 13:17:06SquirrelyWas a tough fight as a lvl 70 druid.  He's immune to cyclone but not warstomp or bash stuns.  Had to use frenzied regen and shift out to heal because it was getting too close.  Trinket is worth coming back to do this quest though, freaking hilarious.\
\
\"And keep the change, you filthy animal.\"\
Classic.",
    "53421483020148302006/12/13 12:36:20NefariousxWeldon Barov is also an easy solo kill for hunters, especially after 2.0 patch.\
\
All the hunter needs to do is wait for the area to clear of alliance, then pull him with Arcane, followed by Serpent and Concussive shot. Sic your pet onto Weldon then just kite him around, drop traps if you wish, not needed but may help add a little advantage, especially if you are entrapment spec'd. Just run around and jump shot concussive, stop for a second to shoot a round or two, then run again. Be sure to keep Cheetah on the whole fight, unless he gets into melee range, then switch to monkey, hit him with a wing clip, and get back to range as quickly as possible. Feign Death if needed, your pet can always be rezzed.\
\
The best place I found to kite him is down by the river, as alliance do not typically travel there and there are no mobs there that will aggro unless you are basically standing ontop of them.\
\
Good luck and have fun!",
    "5342199121111876732007/12/10 14:21:28Sp3cialConfirmed this just now - before the patch I could barely get him to 25%, I just killed him without taking any damage. Level 70 Rogue btw",
    "5342209491111876732007/12/29 18:35:11superaidsI just soloed this quest as a 60 Warlock.  Had to use a healthstone because he is immune to fear.  Easily doable.",
