    "4491187866101878662007/11/19 18:58:47shammanRewards 8150xp as of patch 2.3",
    "44913746131291942007/02/17 10:20:57DantaresIf you fail this quest, abandon it if you havent already and then go back to the spot where you originally found ringo (52, 50)\
\
He wont respawn right away, he takes about 5-10 minutes to respawn.  All you have to do then is talk to him again and re-accept the quest.\
\
However, remember that the canteen itself only lasts for 25 minutes, so it seems that if you abandon and then re-accept the quest, instead of giving you a new canteen, you are stuck with the old canteen on the already partially used-up timer.  You can destroy the old canteen before re-accepting the new quest and he will give you a new one.",
    "449112078110120782006/12/09 10:49:03AlinnarelBeetles Reference - The Song is \"A Little Help from my Friends\" and for the quest you need to find somebody named Ringo :) Props to Blizzard's creativity",
    "449112098911878912007/07/15 10:37:07LieandraYou don't need to have Ringo targeted. You just need to be in his area to use the canteen. The chatbox does help, as Ringo does complain before passing out.",
    "44912919410291942007/02/01 22:59:11ShortinaIf you happen to fail...you can't just run back to ringo..that doesn't do anything! And i just ran back to spraggle frock and i can't start the quest over...any suggestions of what to do if you fail??",
    "449113736120137362006/12/11 23:43:07KarakenRingo is found in a small cave on the mountain in the center of Un'Goro Crater. Check pinktoque's comment on Ringo's page (Click Ringo's name in the \"Quick Facts\" area.) for coordinates.\
\
This is an easy quest. You have to escort Ringo back to Spraggle Frock at Marshal's Refuge within the time limit. Along the way, Ringo will faint, requiring you to use the canteen to revive him. Even with these delays, you still have more then enough time to get to Marshal's Refuge.\
\
Just so you know, the canteen has a cooldown (Around 45 seconds) before it can be used again. If he faints before the cooldown is up, don't panic and just wait for the cooldown to finish.\
\
I like all the references blizzard put in here. There's so many to count.",
    "4491186804101868042007/11/18 04:20:37ManamiI just did the quest and got attacked by allys just outside Marshalls Refuge. And the quest failed... So, im not sure you can continue the quest after you've died. Atleast I couldn't :/ (but apperantly Beerster could :S )\
\
So if you're on a pvp-server, watch out!",
    "4491154583501545832007/09/18 08:39:31NailerRingo says:\
\
When you receiving quest:\
- Well, I'm not sure how far I'll make it in this state... I'm feeling kind of faint...\
- Remember, if I faint again, the water that Spraggle gave you will revive me.\
\
Sometimes, when he will fall to the ground he says one of phrases:\
- The heat... I can't take it...\
- Maybe... you could carry me?\
- Uuuuuuggggghhhhh....\
- I'm not feeling so well...\
\
When he standing up, he can say one of the following:\
- Where... Where am I?\
- I am feeling a little better now, thank you.\
- Yes, I must go on.\
- How am I feeling? Quite soaked, thank you.\
\
And when quest is complete, there are dialog with Spraggle:\
00:00 Ringo: Spraggle! I didn't think I'd make it back!\
00:03 Spraggle Frock: Ringo! You're okay!\
00:08 Ringo: Oh... I'm feeling faint...\
00:09 - Ringo falls on the ground\
00:18 - Ringo standing up\
00:19 Ringo: Ugh.\
00:22 Spraggle Frock: Ringo? Wake up! Don't worry, I'll take care of you.\
01:04 - Ringo disappears...",
