    "82325250npcOgtinc8405npcOgtinc8405635018151281533823148232",
    "8232633823133732006/12/05 15:08:44Aeryn...expanding on what glassthorne posted:\
\
When this quest was first available, all the way to the release of AQ40, there were no replacements for the Devilsaur Eye, and any hunter who took the spear found it quickly replaced, and any hunter who took the Devilsaur Tooth quickly found that it was useless in raids, and nominal in PvP.  However, with the release of AQ40, Naxx, and the expansion, there are several replacements for the Devilsaur Eye.  Examples being: Badge of the Swarmguard, Drake Fang Talisman, Jom Gabber, Kiss of the Spider and Slayer's Crest.  Even outside of raids, the Earthstrike trinket from the Cenarian Circle replaces the Devilsaur Eye.\
\
However, nothing in the game replaces the Devilsaur Tooth.  So, if you are a hunter that has not yet chosen your reward, it is probably in your best interest to get the Devilsaur Tooth.  Even in the expansion, there is not a replacement for this item.",
    "8232337329033732006/11/10 15:21:24glassthorneWhen it comes to your reward choices there are a couple of things to consider.\
\
In my opinion, the Hunting Spear is probably the least useful of the three items.  Weapons themselves will eventually become outdated, to begin with, as people level up, especially with the upcoming expansion.  Also, if one truly wants a decent spear, many hunters go and get the Ice Barbed Spear  (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=19106) which is a reward if you win ONE battle in Alterac Valley.  This spear has better overall stats, in my opinion, than the Hunting Spear, as it has an abundance of agility as well as stamina.\
\
This brings it down to the last two items.  Now if you are a Marks or Surv hunter, the Devilsaur Eye is clearly the best choice for you.  However, I'm not certain if there are other trinkets more useful than this for Marks/Surv hunters, so please make a comment if you believe there is.\
\
Being a BM hunter, I instinctively went for the Devilsaur Tooth.  I have no doubt in my mind that this trinket is one of the best for hunters with this spec.  It's highly useful for opening attacks, especially if one has a cat.  A cat put into Prowl, with the Devilsaur Tooth buff, as well as triggering Bestial Wrath the moment before it reaches the intended target means a strong critical opening attack that will proc Frenzy instantly.\
\
This will become especially useful when the expansion pack is released.  One of the new BM abilities is Ferocious Inspiration.  It means that when your pet scores a critical hit, all party members have their damage output increased by 1-3% for 10 seconds.",
    "8232189886111505002007/11/23 09:58:04exsanguinatorThe eye is definitely the choice to go with. As well as the above statement about the tooth being an extra crit that you don't really, the spear is also no good because  you should have gotten Grimlok's Charge (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=9416) from Uldaman a few levels ago anyway.",
    "82322591240259122007/01/27 18:24:36jerichoIs this still the truth with BC out now?  I know there are two seperate better trinkets than the eye you can get in Outland.  Bladefist's Breath and Mark of Conquest.  Both easy to obtain.  I realise that they are 8 and 10 levels higher than the eye you obtain here.  But does this effect the need for the eye over the tooth?  There still is no trinket I know of that enhances Pet crit rate in BC.",
    "8232212463102124632008/01/03 21:14:31jaffyThe Temple of Atal'Hakkar is also known as [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?zone=1417]The Sunken Temple[/url]",
    "82321505001401505002007/09/08 00:22:10zhekI think there's too many arguments that exist on the premise of an item being \"irreplaceable\". It's said also for the warlock quest, with one trinket being pretty much unique and the other two items being eventually replaceable. But that trinket is a 30 minute cooldown free void walker. My problem with taking the \"irreplaceable\" trinket is that odds are you're not going to wear the thing at higher levels even if you can't replace it. What it does simply isn't special enough to matter.\
\
In this case we have the Eye versus the Tooth. The polearm is pretty bad, nice crit, but while leveling your crit isn't terribly high to begin with. Greens at least increase your AP while they're at it. The Tooth gives a free crit on your pet's next attack. Now, if you're MM, or Survival, this doesn't really matter, your pet isn't a huge amount of your DPS and a crit other then the minor extra damage (especially if it's a claw or bite rather then a melee swing) is tiny. But if you're BM, you're looking at Ferocious Inspiration and Frenzy both procing every crit.\
\
The problem exists that your pet simply can maintain both up a ridiculously large amount of the time without the trinket. Particularly after the first crit, frenzy helps increase the odds he'll proc before the effect is over and refresh the duration. With cobra reflexes, serpent's swiftness, and frenzy, your pet attacks slightly more then once a second (.99 per second). Combined with a focus dump like Claw, and he doesn't need the crit from the Tooth.\
\
I think the Eye is more beneficial while leveling. And odds are if you're looking this up you are doing that. The eye gives a solid benefit and while it's not unique, the fact of the matter is you probably won't be using the Tooth in Outland anyway. You'll end up replacing either trinket but the Eye is a better damage increaser then offering a free crit to a pet that crits all the time anyway.",
    "8232152567611505002007/09/13 16:11:10ElsirI just wanted to say that I completely agree with zhek's opinion on this.  I have levelled a lock to 70 and took the voidwalker trinket on the reasoning that it was irreplaceable.  Guess what?  I never used it, because it sucks.  The devilsaur tooth sucks even more.  You will never equip it at level 70, and either of the other quest rewards are superior for levelling.  It's much better to have an item that will help you for 8-10 levels than one which will never help you, ever.  I am currently levelling a hunter and I plan on taking the trinket.  As a BM-spec hunter, it will stack nicely with BW, TBW, Rapid Fire, and Blood Fury for some insane burst damage!  The spear is a good choice as well if you aren't taking the IBS from the AV quest.",
  },
