    "44921156411117272006/12/08 17:15:14StringAnomalypink, your comments were awesome. To clarify the location of Ringo; the cave he is in is on the map, it is the bottom right most cave. This is not on the top level of Fire Plume Ridge, but located on one of the middle levels you should pass as you walk to the top.",
    "4492137144101371442007/08/13 13:22:59slothkingAlthough this is an escort quest ringo will not fight if you draw arrago therefor you can run by monster with stopping and actually killing it.",
    "44923443316117272007/02/12 02:29:15CinoshOnly thing I'd add is that Ringo doesn't actually have to be targetted for the canteen to work.  He's revived regardless when you use it.",
    "44921779632117272007/11/02 03:51:05TheBadManThis was an excellent comment. Having just done the quest, I would like to add:\
*The little brat is lvl 54, but too cheap to buy a mount, so don't bother with your own. If he falls too far behind, you lose.\
*His cave is visable on your map in the south-eastern corner of Fire Plume Ridge, and if your not a terrible climber you can get at it from the south without drawing any agro.\
*He will say something once or twice before he drops, but before he actually falls over he will stop following you for a second and wander in a random direction, so just left click and glance behind you whenever he complains.\
*I suggest watching the little guy and walking backwards over the ledges on your way down, as the canteen has a very short range, and climbing back up the mountain is annoying.\
*Pick this up on your way back from Alien Ecology http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=3883 to keep your little vacation in Jurassic Park as short as possible.",
    "4492172775017272006/10/10 16:38:55pinktoqueRingo can be found initially in a small cave on Fire Plume Ridge at location 51, 50 to complete the quest to \"find\" him.  Once you find him, he'll give you a new quest \"A Little Help From My Friends\" and you escort him back to Marshal's Refuge. \
\
The escort part isn't tough because you lead Ringo, and so you can avoid mobs on your walk back (and you have like 22 minutes to do it.) You have a little canteen of water in your inventory that you were given from Spraggle when you were sent out to find Ringo, called \"Spraggle's Canteen\"- watch for Ringo to say things like \"Ugghhh\" or \"I'm feeling faint\" ... those are indications that he is about to faint, and will need to be revived with the water from the little canteen in order to proceed. \
\
I put the canteen in an empty slot in my hotbar for the duration of this quest.  I kept Ringo targeted; when he faints, you lose him as a target, so even if I missed his cues like \"uggh ... the heat, it's getting to me...\", as soon as I noticed I'd lost him as a target I knew I needed to revive him.  Simply click on him and then click the canteen in order to give him some water and revive him.  \
\
Easy as pie :)",
