    "763460npcHastat the Ancient14526npcHastat the Ancient145269950",
    "763467775067772006/12/05 21:42:02UrogThe Mature Blue Dragon Sinew used to make this quiver drops from Azuregos (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=6109), The Cobalt Scalebanes in Mazthoril, Winterspring (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=18704) or a friendly guildmate. If your guild can easily take down Azuregos, I suggest not farming endless hours in Mazthoril. If you have extra gold floating around, these seem to go anywhere from 80g to 800g.",
    "7634124474201244742007/07/21 10:59:42dainer09Even to this day after the release of the expansion, this is the best out there, only tied by http://www.wowhead.com/?item=29143 for the horde and http://www.wowhead.com/?item=29144 for the alliance. Now, its a lot easier to obtain the one from your Nagrand faction, but if you ever come across the Mature Blue Dragon Sinew, I would sugest to try and sell it, but you may not have the best of luck with it since its easier to obtain these, so really, its all up to you.\
\
~Lerex",
    "7634127750201277502007/07/27 12:26:33Jivocan you only get the quiver if you have the leaf from mc?\
