    "352847713171446522007/03/07 14:25:03InfernoManactually need to make a correction, seemed like a good tip before I did the encounter, then when we went to start it, realized this was not true. You need to use the egg in the room where the skeleton of the avatar is in order to start the encounter, and then the mobs start spawning. Unless it was meant that you need to clear all the mobs around the area. \
\
This encounter is VERY hectic if you aren't well organized, so make sure you brief everyone before using the egg. \
Change the loot to free for all(thanks to the second post) and make sure one person is in charge of getting the blood and extinguishing the torches. The blood drops from wyvern looking creatures called Hakkari Bloodkeepers(http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=8438) that spawn one at a time. there are also several non elite venom spitters running around, that will quickly target your priest/healer, so have at least one person assigned to pull these off of them. Also, during the encounter before Hakkar is summoned by putting out the four torches, there are elite dragonkin called Nightmare Suppressor's (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=8497#00Rzc) that spawn and try to prevent you from summoning the avatar, they also start a \"drain soul\" like animation on the Avatar, but I didn't really notice if it was doing anything with all the other mobs around, sorry. But if you see them doing the drain, a quick attack is all that is needed to break the action and have them target you, then it is just a regular elite fight. \
One last thing, make sure everyone is ready and aware before the person with the blood goes to put the last torch out, because as soon as it is extinguished, the once ghost-form of the avatar hovering in the center of the room comes to life and starts pounding on the nearest target, so make sure your healer/ mages, or any other cloth wearers are well back.  And this also gives you a chance to change the loot back to group loot before having to face the big guy (something I wish I had done) He drops some nice Rare BoP items, and it is kind of a bummer to have someone accidentally loot it without realizing it is still on free for all.  Good luck and hope this makes the encounter a little easier for anyone else.",
    "3528275340027532006/11/04 09:27:37mootwoThis is part of a long chain quest designed to familiarize you with Zul'Gurub and the Zandalar Tribe. Much of the rewards are decent for their level. The Faded Hakkari Cloak is only slightly worse than everyone's favorite Hide of the Wild. Definitely a worthwhile chain for someone that doesn't want to shell out for the Hide.\
\
Here's the full quest chain:\
 - Screecher Spirits(Feralas) - http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=3520\
 - The Prophecy of Mosh'aru(Zul'Farrak) - http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=3520\
 - The Ancient Egg(Hinterlands) - http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=4787\
 - The God Hakkar(Temple of Atal'Hakkar) - http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=3528\
 - The Lost Tablets of Mosh'aru(Eastern Plaguelands) - http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=5065\
 - The Final Tablets(Lower Blackrock Spire) - http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=4788\
 - Confront Yeh'kinya(Tanaris) - http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=8181\
 - The Hand of Rastakhan(Stranglethorn Vale) - http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=8182",
    "3528141354201413542007/08/20 19:27:08moenbaseAfter you turned in the quest and talk to the NPC again, you can optional take another item.\
He hints that you need to kill the avatar of Hakkar again.\
I haven't done this part since it doesn't really appears to be a quest.\
Does anyone know what's it about?\
The item you get is: http://www.wowhead.com/?item=10818",
    "3528186311101863112007/11/17 11:57:37LysdexicAs of 2.3, this quest gives 11,400 XP.",
    "352864091190640912007/04/08 22:09:06BadgerPLEASE NOTE - If you wipe during this encounter, you will NOT be able to do it again until the instance is reset.",
    "35284465250446522007/03/01 15:36:05ZoozTake this hint people , dont ever use the egg till all the mobs around are killed .. casue like many of mobs will respwan adn tehy will stay respwaning till the 4 fires are off :) .. good luck",
    "3528143627311413542007/08/25 00:48:14CyberjetGetting the scroll simply lets you summon the Avatar of Hakkar again if you choose to do so. It is always a good idea to grab this from the quest NPC after you have turned this in, just to have it laying around if you want to go back into ST.",
    "35288903108902006/09/22 16:33:26contentiousMaybe I'm silly for not catching onto this, but...\
