    "614152001101520012007/09/12 08:20:20cheekyprincessThe NPC to start this quest is Captain Hecklebury Smotts (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=2500) at 26, 73 in Booty Bay, STV. =)",
    "614207128102071282007/12/25 16:00:29SevenUPsoloed by 42 lock. Realy easy :P",
    "614198505301985052007/12/09 11:55:57BellonaFound Gorlash at 36,70  Could not take him down with my lvl 45 Warrior soloing even with Retaliation up.",
    "6141133991101133992007/06/30 14:00:45remyThe directions are precise. And he's definitely hard to miss.\
\
If you have sucky bracers and could use those [see required level: 35], or if you're just lazy and impatient, you could kite him back to the entrance of the Booty Bay entrance. The goblins will take care of him.\
\
Gorlash can rooted, stunned, slowed and novaed. Take caution to stay clear of the Bloodsail mobs. You might outrun them too but you might be slowed as well.",
    "614209159102091592007/12/29 04:55:56KyoraHe's now a level 42 elite and I solo'd him as a level 43 paladin but I used everything I had including lay on hands. Didn't have any potions or it would have been easier.",
    "614144586601445862007/08/27 00:54:16CorrodiasThis quest gives +150 Booty Bay rep and -150 Bloodsail Buccaneers rep.",
    "614183832101838322007/11/14 00:16:35EvalaraAs of 2.3 Gorlash is a level 42 elite.  I solo'd him as a 41 feral druid by cat dpsing, bear stun, entangling roots, heal, repeat.",
    "614126905301269052007/07/26 00:52:38Flinxslwarlocks: he's fearable, easy quest :)",
    "6141347281401347282007/08/09 03:59:28gothicgorlash in 36.69",
    "614149599201495992007/09/05 23:04:48GenericNPCSoloable by a 46 Feral Druid.\
\
I will admit my gear is somewhat twinked, but nothing too outrageous. 3,480 health in Dire Bear Form, 24% crit.\
\
Start in caster form, Entangling Root, Moonfire. Recast Roots when the timer is almost up, and repeat this until he's maybe at 85-90%. After that just wait out until Roots is almost up, cast Regrowth and Rejuv on your and pop Bear Form tossing a (Feral) Faerie Fire on him (don't Enrage).\
\
Demoralize him as soon as you can. Bash him right after, and begin Mauling. When YOU are at about half health gather up about 30-40 Rage and hit your Enrage + Frenzied Regeneration. Auto-swing until it's over. Then start the mauling again.\
\
After that just make sure you keep blowing your CDs (Bash and Enrage primarily), and always keep Demoralizing Roar and Faerie Fire on him. If it starts getting close at the end, you can always pop out, root him, run out of melee, and heal. And if you're Tauren, of course War Stomp first thing when you pop out. ;]\
\
It's a lot easier than all these words make it seem. Just make sure you've been stacking your agi and stam like you should. :P",
    "614211787111495992008/01/02 18:55:42paulnkim1993Soloed by a 46 hunter with 45 pet.  Sent in the cat, when she had his attention i started pounding him.  When Cat died he came at me but didn't have much left.",
    "614396742039672006/11/21 13:38:26OrmrissTo find Gorlash, leave Booty Bay from the tunnel, then head to the east coast.  You should pass through an area with Bloodsail mages/swashbucklers.  As soon as you hit the beach, start running north.  You should see Gorlash walking around in the ocean (he's huge and hard to miss).\
\
Gorlash is a level 47 elite giant, so come prepared.  Two shamans (mid to late 40s) did this with no problems.  Probably a good idea to bring some healing.  Total time from getting quest, finding and killing Gorlash, then returning is maybe ten minutes.",
