    "9053151750311493342007/09/11 16:10:23BrighidWell, do keep in mind that some people don't run instances quite so often, so the Grizzled Pelt may still be a good choice.\
\
Though, Feral Druids sometimes are asked to main heal (I can attest that it is quite viable to do, from my own experience), so if one prefers not to get the Grizzled Pelt, the Forest's Embrace could be a good alternative.\
\
I agree with your evaluation of the items, though.",
    "9053166482411493342007/10/12 09:24:48dlwightAs a feral druid, I would have to disagree with you.  In the whole debate of strength vs agility for feral druids, I calculated that you generally want to maximize the sum of str + agi for max dps.  That being said, the grizzled pelt has a slight dps advantage at a sum of 33, while the mixologist's tunic is 29.  On the other hand, you get 70 more health with the mixologist's tunic from the extra stamina and 7 more armor, but the grizzled pelt has slightly more agility which also boosts your armor.  So in the end, I would argue that they are virtually identical for feral druids and since you will probably have to compete with your other party members for the mixologist's tunic, I would favor taking the Grizzled pelt now.",
    "9053195391201953912007/12/03 12:00:17duathorthadTo be honest, the rewards for the druid version of this quest are less than sterling. I was hoping for a useful trinket (as seems to be offered for all other classes), but instead we got easily replaceable items :(\
\
Definetely not as great when compared to what a priest or mage is offered.",
    "905369394200693942007/04/18 23:52:07NimfoThe order of the statues is:\
\
(on mini map)\
\
6 oclock - 12 oclock - 8 oclock - 4 oclock - 10 oclock - 2 oclock\
\
If you're doing it right ~ the statues will light up green as you go ~ I wrote them down exactly opposite by accident and was very frustrated.  Hope this helps!",
    "9053149334101493342007/09/05 08:30:38BoyneWas looking for better gear to see what would be the best choice.\
\
For healing gear, the bonus to healing on the Forest's Embrace is godlike. You won't find anything even close until Outland, when you can get Sacred Feather Vest (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=28050).\
\
If you're Balance, take the staff. The bonuses on it are very nice, and while you will replace it with Crystfire Staff (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=24069) in Outland, it will easily last until then.\
\
If you're feral, DON'T take the Grizzled Pelt. Mixologist's Tunic (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=12793), which drops in BRD, is much better. You'll be replacing the Pelt very quickly. Frankly I'd take the staff, as it sells for the most. >.<",
    "905330146030142006/11/06 10:03:13NiekonFun and interesting quest to deal with. Ran this with a warrior. After clearing most of the bottom area we went up and began clearing around the statues.\
\
Be careful of mobs that travel a path. We learned that the hard way when a slime came around the corner unexpectedly. And there is an order to the statues that must be followed.\
\
Before activating the last statue, be sure nothing has re-spawned down below on the steps or in the water. If clear, activate the last statue click into cat form and jump down (softer landing) and try to not get punted by the mob that spawned. The punt won't kill you... the fall from being punted will.\
\
The good thing about this quest is that it's near the beginning of the instance and as long as everyone knows what they are doing things will roll along smoothly.",
    "9053131618501316182007/08/03 10:30:06VaidemineHere's the link to the AtlasMod map that shows the order of the statues to summon the boss you need for the Putrid Vine:\
\
http://atlasmod.com/Maps/TheSunkenTemple.jpg",
    "9053164322201643222007/10/07 14:51:27munkeymanIn case you don't want to risk having the pool respawn in the middle of your battle with the guardian (this happened to my party and the spawns hit our healer so fast that the rest of us wiped in no time), when we came back, we did it the opposite way. We cleared upstairs first and then had someone activate all but the final statue, while the rest of the party jumped down to take on the mobs. Then, when the pool was clear, the last statue was activated and our last guy jumped down to take on the guardian. Easy after that.",
  },
