    "76318594611728552007/05/19 22:36:25darukaruYeah, you don't actually receive these as in-bag items. You can buy the black lodestone at the last stage of the quest, and if you buy the imp jar that supposedly has your bell/wheel/candle in it.",
    "76319610914124302007/06/02 18:42:54ForgeryThis isn't exactly accurate.  The quests to get the Bell the Candle and the Wheel must be completed as prerequisites to getting this quest.   The summoning agents that you don't need to purchase are the Jar, the Lodestone, and the Glyphs.  As long as you have a warlock with you that has these items, you don't need them, meaning you can save 250g!\
