    "608189290111839152007/11/22 05:02:54KintaConfirmed this one while on the quest. The only thing higher than level 42 were the two other spawns that were right next to the captain. Their names elude me at the moment, but one was an Orc, and one was a Tauren =] This quest is infinitely easier since the patch. The captains and the normal spawns were all 40-42.",
    "60819741811391002007/12/07 11:44:22RandithynsThey must have changed this. As a lvl 43 rogue, I stealthed by everyone, got in a corner in the fleet masters room, so not another mob could see me, I unstealthed and killed him easy.  He is now level 42 and I didn't aggro any other mobs.  Easy kill in the middle ship.",
    "608206286102062862007/12/23 23:40:44WasabiiSoloed him as a lvl 41 Prot Pali (2.6k health 4.8k armor). Sol/JoL were enough to keep me on par with his health, actually I ditched Sol for SoW halfway through, HS had drained my mana. Shielded and healed twice when he crit with a melee and then trample. Other wise he hit for about 90-110 crit for around 200 didn't catch how much trample did.\
