    "6089212611822852007/05/28 01:48:34KineticTrying to solo this quest below level 45 is a complete waste of time. I highly engourage you to bring a friend or two along due to the amount of adds you'll be dealing with. It's very hard to manage to pull 1-2 mobs within the boat where all the pirates patrol around and chain-pull even more mobs. If you're 45+ then this quest definitely is soloable - but depending on your class you might spend some time corpse running. And as stated above - make sure to have all the other pirate related quests and complete them as doing this one and what comes to the Riddle - I found it at Stillwater's ship.",
    "608189410101894102007/11/22 10:35:25sigmardinThis is all confirmed, its a simple quest now, the only small struggle would be the fact that the mobs are still close to each other and they respawn extremely quickly.\
   -- On a side note, there is a Solid Chest in the bottom floor of the ship with Fleet Master Firallon on it.  I didnt get any thing spectacular from it, but it did give me 2 greater healing pots, and some moonberry juice, some mageweave,and 2 greater mana pots.\
