So just to be safe, remove your disguise before Isillien engages Taelan and stand back.",
    "58621408040140802006/12/12 12:02:03granger1When you get to the tower Fordring will call out some scarlet crusade 63 elite.  just watch the show as with the Onyxia key chain.  Fordring will die but you can usually just stay far enough away to stay out of combat.  After Fordring dies, just wait for his dad to come riding up and lay the smack down.  He well kill everyone then if your still alive just go talk to him to claim your awesome reward!",
    "586214735150147352006/12/13 08:06:33dotsBEFORE  YOU DO THIS QUEST...\
\
You can use the disguise that Myranda the Hag gives you to finish two other XP-rich quests in \"EZ mode\".\
\
The Mark of the Lightbringer - Part 1/2 - lvl 58 req\
(http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=9474)\
Requires you to get a box in one of the towers along the road.\
6200xp + 250 rep/Exodar, with an easy follow-up quest worth another 7750xp + 350rep\
\
Unfinished Business - Part 3/3 - lvl 55 req\
(http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=6025) \
Asks you to go up the tower that's in the middle of Hearthglen and face the main gates.\
6200xp for an elite quest and all you have to do is walk through some friendly 55-60 elites.\
\
I strongly recommend you complete both these quests before you talk to Fordring in Hearthglen, as you can't stray too far from him once he begins the escort quest. And in the worst secnario, if you get ganked, you can still run back to get another disguise from Myranda.\
\
Last note, do NOT remove your disguise when Tirion tells you to. It is NOT necessary and only makes the escort harder. The down side is that you cannot loot the bodies along the escort becase you did not aggro them, however, I find it's a small price to pay for a little extra assurance I won't die from mobs (especially at the last part when he, himself dies to mobs 9_9\")",
    "586212197461147352007/07/17 03:06:33ladenedgeNB: doing The Mark of the Lightbringer while disguised no longer works.  Interacting with the box at the top of the tower immediately removes your disguise and alerts the nearby mobs.",
