  ["The Balance of Light and Shadow60"] = {
    "762260npcEris Havenfire14494npcEris Havenfire144949950",
    "762247181212006/09/15 10:10:04IncendiumGood point, however, each priest doing the quest must have either the eye or the spectral essence. It is confirmed that you do not all need the same item to work on the quest together.",
    "76227015510701552007/04/20 15:52:05RaydawnOkay, first, I used only four spells. Holy Nova Rank 6 for the skellies, Flash Heal Rank 4, and Renew Ranks 9 and 6.\
\
The Peasants: You cannot use the \"V\" key to see their health bars. I tried this every which way. Instead, I use the AF Tool Tip mod. This brings the tooltip (with hp) to your mouse pointer, so you can scan across the wave of peasants and see their health without moving your eyes to the lower right corner. The gauntlet of skeletal archers tend to focus on 1-3 targets, and you can see their arrows sticking out so that helps you decide who to heal as well. Begin healing with Renew unless the peasant is very close to death. Use Renew 9 if they're getting beat up a lot/diseased, especially if they are members of a \"fresh\" wave. Use Rank 6 renew for \"stale\" peasants who are diseased or hurt. I used Flash Heal only if they were very low (followed up with a Renew 9) or if they were being fired out by lots of archers and diseased, etc. I think I used disease cure only twice out of nervousness, so I'm sure it's not very necessary. Use your best judgement once you get a feel for the event.\
\
The skeletons: I used Crystal Charge, made from the red and yellow power crystals in Un'Goro crater. I didn't use Oil of Immolation because I wasn't sure if they were on the same cooldown as Major Mana Potions, so I didn't risk it. When they are grouped up, a crystal charge or holy nova is great. When my cooldown for the Crystal Charge (1 min) was still going down, I was forced to use Holy Nova. I used Rank 6, but Rank 5 MIGHT work. Wanding is key. It took usually 1, sometimes 2 hits from my Bonecreeper Stylus (which is why I say that Holy Nova Rank 5 just might do enough damage). This works especially great if you can see a lone skelly running down to you and the overall health of the peasant wave is good and you can just wand him as he comes. Resists stink, and sometimes you have to let a skelly wail on you while you throw some renews around.\
\
Extras: I used 3-4 Major Mana Potions, I honestly can't remember. Use them early, so the cooldown ticks while you fight. I also used Lesser Mana Oil (8mp5) on my weapon. I'm sure some Nightfin Soup (8mp5) would be a big help as well. I didn't use Demonic or Dark Runes, but I'm sure those would help too.\
\
Good luck!",
    "7622113837401138372007/07/01 12:11:03ShaarlalYou can use Shift-V to have the peasents heal toggled on. It helps immensly",
    "762250761212006/09/16 04:20:25tompsterI couldn't see the NPC without the Eye of Divinity. I do have Spectral essence and the Eye of shadow. Doesn't work :(",
    "7622107813010782006/09/27 07:50:25halldorrYou NEED the EoD, it was changed a patch or two ago. While I can't find it mentioned specifically but was probably stealth nerfed in 1.11.2 when they fixed another issues with Spectral Essence: http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/patchnotes/patch1p11.html as I couldn't see them with my Spectral Essence equipped.",
    "762269551212006/09/19 08:11:26tompsterI've checked quite many times now, but no luck... Early in the morning, late in the evening. Guess I'll just go get EoD first. Could they have changed this on 1.12 patch?",
    "7622687306872006/09/19 05:16:17bollerI tried this as well, doesn't seem to work I'm afraid.",
    "762232832032832006/11/09 14:57:55L124RDThe quest is fairly easy to do. I recommend failing it once so you get a feel for what's going on. It's basically a more complicated version of the triage quest you did to get your bandaging up.\
\
There are several methods that are available online for how to complete this quest, but let me say what worked for me:\
1) 60 Feral Druid in bear form at the cave entrance who was kind enough to go /afk there while he made dinner\
2) In order: Full rank renew on purples, abolish greens, ~half rank renew on injured.\
3) If your bear form druid friend is taking significant damage, through him a heal or full rank renew.\
\
When the skeletons attack you, there are significantly fewer arrows flying through the air. By leaving the bear at the entryway, he will pick up all of the skeletons and keep them for quite a while making keeping up the peasants significantly easier.\
\
Using this method, I blew 1 mana potion and the Mar'li's Eye. I was in all 5-man blues, except for 1 piece of prophecy and my wonderful green gloves (and Mar'li's Eye... and the friendly ring of the Bronze Dragonflight)",
    "76221670820167082006/12/18 02:29:06jsounds2010Few things that helped me complete the quest on my 1st try.\
\
1) Get tinytip: an addon that allows you to see the health bars when you scroll your mouse over the peasants.  For some reason you can'y use V, shift-V, or control-V to see the health bars anymore.  I've read Dev's posts that say the will address it in an upcoming patch, but they haven't yet.\
2) Oil of Immolation: there's no cooldown & with these the Skellies go down quick.\
3) Holy Nova rank 3: in case you run out of Oil of Im, but it drains much needed mana. Mana conservation was the toughest part for me\
4) Renew Rank 5, Flash heal Rank 4: You don't need full ranks for peasants they don't have much health\
5) Well placed PychScream: If you get overwhelmed by Skellies & you need mana for peasant heals\
6) Wand: Takes down single skellies in 1 hit usually\
7) Respawn of quest NPC, if you fail,  is much quicker now : used to be over an hour.  Now it's no more than 30mins.\
8) Net videos of the quest: found lots of great ones\
9) Cure 1st Heal 2nd: Make sure you cure the peasants 1st, then heal.  The diseases they get will wipe them out quick.\
10) Peasants will die:  Don't worry if you loose 1 or 2 in each group.     \
11) Have a couple mana potions & use the 1st one as soon as your mana is @ 50%: That way your cooldown will be up when/if you run out of mana\
GL!",
    "76222180212006/09/12 11:22:09IncendiumThis quest is possible to do without the eye of divinity. Complete this (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=5384) quest, and equip the Spectral Essence.\
\
Be careful, as the NPC who spawns this quest has a 2 hour respawn and WILL despawn if anyone attempting the quest fails it.",
    "7622127772132832006/12/10 13:45:59WailanerThis quest is now much easier with Holy Nova. If you decide to solo this and it is completely possible here are some hints. Use renew rank 3 on the peasants this will be enough health for them to reach safety and enough aggro for you to get the skeleton attention. When your shield gets eat'en up by the skeleton and you threw out your renews blow the skeletons away with Holy Nova. The skeletons do not have much HP.\
\
Only problem with soloing the event is the long reset time if you fail. Therefore it is nice to bring a couple friends. From what I understand the rules are the friends should stand on top of the quest giver and not move during the event and they are not to heal you. Have a mage and another healer the mage can AOE on top of you when the skeletons come and the addition healer can heal the mage. This way you can save all your mana for peasants.",
    "762240671212006/09/14 22:49:24ExcorsismAlso, don't forget that it is doable with other priests in the party. For example, one priest would be moving to heal the peasants as they walk their way towards the safe zone while the other # of priests will stand at whatever location they please to heal the incoming peasants that walk to the exit. The priest that is only able to move is the one who started the quest.\
\
The spawn timer was reduced by a significant amount, presumably to around 10 minutes now. I'm not sure on this, though.",
