    "7862209787212013792007/12/30 09:19:22qillerdaemonAs with any glitch like this, like npc's that you can't see go down or can't loot, try to log out and log back in. This resets the WoW client on your computer back with the realm's database server. It's annoying, but it often gives you the npc or loot, or in your case, your quest.",
    "78621697741901697742007/10/16 12:48:17odinsgrudgeAs of 2.3 the mobs for this quest are no longer elite.",
    "7862201379102013792007/12/14 20:57:46Effen5674anyone else had problems accepting this quest? When i click on the \"A Call To Arms!\" poster, and try to accept the quest, it doesnt do anything? A Glitch maybe?",
    "7862402625040262006/11/22 23:14:43OrmrissExpect to spend a couple of hours doing this one, unless you bring a big and/or overpowered group with you.  The mobs are level 46-50 elites, and you have to take down 80 of them total.  Just work your way to the top of Jintha'alor and you will find all your mobs.  You may have to backtrack in places to pick up respawns since you need so many kills.\
\
The Soul Eaters and Blood Drinkers are on the last two levels.  Soul Eaters have an ability very similar to Mana Burn, so watch out casters.  Blood Drinkers tend to hit hard and often, so be ready with heals.  My level 55 shaman, with about 3800 armor, was getting hit for about 150 a pop.\
\
The Berserkers and Shadow Hunters are on the two levels preceding the Soul Eaters/Blood Drinkers.  The Blood Drinkers are similar to Fury Warriors, while the Shadow Hunters will use ranged attacks unless you close to melee range.  For some reason, the Hunters can also cast Shadow Word: Pain.\
\
The quest is long but you can stack this with several other quests out of Revantusk Village.  If you just make your way to the altar at the top, you'll likely end up getting about a quarter of the 80 kills you need.  The trinket reward is great for all melee classes, but casters not so much.  You do get over 2g for completion though, so unless you wipe a bunch you should come out ahead.  Not to mention all that xp from killing 80 elite mobs.\
\
For the record, I completed this with a 51 and 55 shaman.  Easy to pull the mobs one at a time.  Just watch for patrols.",
