    "6521977290197722007/01/08 03:09:13entropicdragonCompleting this will unlock the next quest in the series, \"Myzrael's Allies\" (horde http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=688, alliance http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=653).",
    "652136510101365102007/08/12 14:40:02E0m3rHere is a Nice trick:\
If you are a Hunter Beastmastery it would be easy though....\
Leave a Trap in front of fozruk's Healer.Then send the pet at the Fozruk's tank partener.You kill the caster.If you are low HP just Feign Death and let your pet harrass the mob.If you succeed into killing the three mobs then you can easily do a mana and health break and then solo the Fozruk.\
If you are a Priest you must be at least 43 level to kill fozruk easily.Fear at 43 level makes all the Fozruk's parteners run away.Fozruk doesn't.So empty all the mana pool on him and be sure to put shield just before fearing the mobs because he can break it with 3-4 hits.",
    "652170711201707112007/10/17 21:14:37Raptorgsince patch 2.3 no longer elite, however not to be underestimated\
\
his caster adds have roughly 150 health(no kidding, i could 1-hit them) and his warrior add has about 200(i just couldn't 1-hit him)\
\
however, Fozruk has 2.4k health and some nasty abilities and high armor, but weak melee, all in all not a tough fight, my suggestion is if you have aoe, focus on Fozruk and use aoe to kill the adds, if you don't have aoe, kill each add seperately, they aren't tough at all\
\
watch out when completing the quest, a giant with roughly 1.5k health will pop up, i almost died because i was at low health",
    "652202281102022812007/12/16 10:23:47savagyThe name of the mob that spawns upon quest completion is Thenan.",
    "652117481111009352007/07/08 13:27:05nelorkyYou can also do the same thing as a priest with Mind Control. Mind Control each of the guards until the rest walk away, kill, rinse and repeat.",
    "6528617531493052007/05/20 09:32:47elarenThe above coordinates are incorrect. The Keystone is located at the Circle of Inner Binding at 36.1, 58.1.",
    "6529219130921912007/05/28 04:04:05blupacheOK, maybe things have changed since the patch, but there's more to this quest then just killing Fozruk. With a 37 prot pally (me), 38 pally, 38 shammie & 37 holy priest we snuffed Fozruk & his little posse without too much hassle.\
\
The holy priest & I went back to hand in. As soon as I clicked on complete, a second 42 elite giant appeared and attacked us. We put him down, priest handed in the quest & clicked complete - the same thing repeated itself.\
\
From the comments on allakhazam, I was expecting a neutral giant to appear - I wasn't expecting him to appear *red* and immediately attack us. But apparently nowadays he is, so if you can't solo a 42 elite then be sure to take your group back to the hand in with you.\
\
Oh, and do remember to click on the keystone again after the fight to pick up the follow on quest chain. We nearly forgot & it's not readily apparent.",
    "652200697102006972007/12/13 12:09:11KaynosI just kill the guy, could'nt loot it, wtf ?!!?!",
    "65251111051112006/11/29 06:45:57XFGREAPERKilling Fozruk is fairly simple with a few 35-38's regardless of class. Kill/Fear/pettank his guards and concentrate on Fozruk. DOT's or a good pet can take out his guards. The Keystone is located with the Earth Elementals and is in the center. Use the Same group to complete and the elementals are nothin.",
    "6528705510870552007/05/21 20:10:17weetabixAs long as you kill the guards first fozruk is fairly easy to solo. With my 40 hunter I killed healer, then mage, then melee, using fd between each one.\
\
Fozruk himself hits fairly hard, and does a stun with a fairly long range that is nasty if you are trying to kite him. Scatter shot and ice trap work fine on him though so easy to get back to range if he does stun you.",
    "6523849030384902007/02/19 03:05:06akmdwA lvl 42 elite spawns either after you complete the quest, or click on the shard to get the next quest, so be prepared.",
    "652207533102075332007/12/26 09:48:52SgtownConfirmed. In 2.3.0, you must kill him and loot him before killing his adds OR kill his adds before him.\
\
When I killed him the first time, I kill the adds then tried to loot and it didn't work. The second time, I killed him then looted just fine, then killed the adds. For testing, I waited around and did it again. I was able to loot him if I killed ALL the adds before Fozruk.\
\
The adds have 150-160 HP.",
    "652192728101927282007/11/28 11:10:20alarinai killed him but i couldn't loot him, by the way as a lvl 39 hunter i was able to solo him just bring some hp potion it'll help you",
    "652191848101918482007/11/26 19:35:10EthernalJust killed the guy, was able to loot",
    "652198803101988032007/12/09 23:23:21Keylordsoloed after 4 tries as a lvl 38 rogue, he wanders between the elemental circles",
    "6522024830202482007/01/11 19:14:57ZannRathI must be a total newb, because I had a time and a half killing fozruk. >_<\
\
No one in AH wanted to kill him, so I was stuck at lv 39 with 42 warrior and 37 rogue. It took a while, but we finally did it. Here's a neat trick that works will to kill his guards, but it requires a rogue, probably with improved sap. I don't know if this will work without.\
\
Find Fozruk and his guards just as he's leaving one of the circles of binding. Sap one of his guards, and everyone will leave the sapped guard behind. Once fozruk is a short distance away, out of relative aggro range, kill the sapped guard. They will continue walking, oblivious. Do this for all of the guards, then you can take on Fozruk solo.\
\
But you HAVE to be quick about this, because the guards respawn when he reaches the next circle of binding.",
    "652191154101911542007/11/25 17:34:29Xion89I tried this quest tonight, and I couldn't loot fozruk. must be a bug with the game or something.",
