    "973760npcLady Liadrin17076npcLady Liadrin170768300Silvermoon City250197212972239723497255973569736797379735160npcLady Liadrin17076npcLady Liadrin170768300Silvermoon City250197212972239723497255973569736797379736160npcLady Liadrin17076npcLady Liadrin170764950Silvermoon City15019721297223972349725597356973679737",
    "9737190609111889122007/11/24 20:25:28Rayzeel60 Prot paladin and 60 Holy paladin did it tonight.",
    "9737208283102082832007/12/27 16:02:36LokthI was a little confused at first because I never ran many 60 instances. The best entrance to use is the Service Entrance that is marked by the cave southeast of the huge Stratholme writing on the map in the Eastern Plaguelands. You need the key to the city or a rogue to use this entrance, however. It was green to my 375 lockpicking rogue. \
\
Upon entering, open the gate immediately inside the instance, kill the first group of mobs, and you're ready to roll for the quest because the chapel is right next past the mobs you just killed on the right. It's a big stone building that looks like..well, a chapel. Go in, use the stuff, kill the dude, then five elites spawn. Kill them and you're set like jet. Had no trouble at all with a 62 ret pally and 70 mutilate rogue.",
    "9737196488211837202007/12/05 14:08:29JilkonConsidering Barthilas who DROPS the key is on the undead side, this comment is made of fail and untruth",
    "9737182050201820502007/11/10 16:55:25piratesbootyone thing that noone mentioned and would only matter with a few select ppl is that THERE ARE 2 GATES that ya need to get thru... this isnt a big deal if ya have a key or rogue.... BUT my pally is a engineer and was using seaforium charges to get thru.... i only took 1 bomb and it sucked... try the suicide thing to res on other side but when ya enter instance it auto resses ya so .. moral of story is if ya usin seaforium charges to get by the gates bring two or else you will be kikin ya self in the arse!!!",
    "9737207862111837202007/12/26 22:12:53GhostlightPa4o4o's comment is correct - you can reach the 'undead' side from the main gate by heading east, and you can then fight Barthilas by the chapel for a key.  \
Barthilas only retreats further into the city when you enter from the side entrance - mostly because otherwise he would be really easy to farm.",
    "9737198070101980702007/12/08 14:11:40GnomeThumperA little clarification.  Once you zone in there are [u]2 sets[/u] of \"double gates\" that you will have to move through.  Once you move out from zone in the first set is down on the [b]right[/b] at the first intersection, Both gates in the \"set\" are locked, they are not trapped, once unlocked they stay unlocked but will auto close, anyone can right click to reopen at that point.  \
\
Once through that \"set\" down a ways on your [b]right[/b] is another \"set\" of double gates(these are open), no traps, once you clear down to these gates simply walk through.  The Chapel is just ahead of you on the right.  There was a named up front when we did it, fairly easy kill for a 70 rogue and me a 60 pally.\
\
Once inside the chapel its pretty anti-climatic from there,  you douse the flame, the pally inside attacks (easy kill), the 6 pallies outside show up, again extremely easy kills.  Rogue never went below 95% health and all dead in less than a minute from start of the event.  The toughest part is clearing down and thats a breeze if you take your time and don't get carried away.",
    "9737176254111747592007/10/29 01:30:05SlatoxYeah, definately doable with a decent 70.  I did it at 60 with a 70 rogue (has has about half epics, 2 epic daggers).  We had to clear the mobs in front in 2 goes, running out once after I ran out of mana (prot spec).  My (combat dagger) rogue friend didn't have any trouble killing the 5 pallies and I only used half my mana to keep him up.\
\
Don't worry if you can't get a full group.",
