    "973731634210316342007/02/06 09:13:05shampThe Alonsus Chapel is located at undead part of Startholme, it's a chapel like building right after first gate. Get your party inside and let paladin burn the house down. Dude inside will agro, kill him. After this some other npcs will spawn outside and whine about you burning their church. After you dispose of them (only one wave) you'll have your quest completed.\
\
Amazing how easy this is compared to alliance paladin quest (which I assume at this point is pretty much same as shamans skyfury helmet quest).",
    "9737210349202103492007/12/31 08:00:21NinoaThis is a purely informative post for freshly dinged 60 paladins with a 70 buddy that hope to pull off the Stratholme boss by themselves. \
\
I have a level 70 feral druid (S1/S2 gear) and just succesfully helped my 60 retri paladin partner with getting his charger. The paladin mostly just stood and watched because he had just switched to a new weapon and had to train his swords so he couldn't hit a thing. :P I handled the groups of skeletons by going cat and taking the non-elites out first. You can use bear form if you want to be safe but I didn't really find it that necessary. Once the paladin started the event, the first boss (he's alone) is a total pushover. After that, the 6 paladins spawned, but I was fine taking them out one by one in bear form. I believe one of them healed (possibly more, can't say for sure), so try to watch out for that. I never really came close to having to heal.\
\
I believe most decently geared melee classes can pull this off just fine (especially if the paladin actually contributes). Casters may have a problem with handling the 6 adds, so you may want to bring a tank in that case. \
\
I strongly recommend going with someone that has the Key to the City so you can enter through the back entrance. The paladin's quest boss is right at the start of the back entrance. If your 70 buddy doesn't have the key, suggest them to go grab it from Magistrate Barthilas ( http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=10435 ). He'll be spawned in the same area as the paladin's quest boss if you enter Stratholme with a party that does not have the Key to the City. Your 70 buddy should be able to dodge most if not all mobs on the way. When your 70 buddy has killed Magistrate Barthilas and looted the key, he can use it to open the gate on the right side of the chapel and leave the instance. He then should be able to open the gates that are keeping you from entering Stratholme via the back entrance. Congrats!",
    "9737210471102104712007/12/31 12:06:22savagy1) Bring friends.\
2) Go through backdoor, much much faster.",
    "97355535150553512007/03/22 11:28:14EmpiriusWell it is soloable if you are lvl 60 and protspec as well.\
I ran in and died inside the room.\
I then ran back and revived near the doorentrance where i would not aggro.\
I then summon my mechanical yeti and looted the vial while he was killed, then i shielded and fled.\
I died in the process of fleeing as well, but mostly due to the fact that i got lost in there and pulled about a bazillion mobs...",
    "97357065111636772007/04/21 19:37:54AchmatovaSoloed as a lvl 60 retribution paladin (some outlands green gear from AH + blade of misfortune). Follow lily instructions to reach the place, then you have to battle 3 elite mobs, any class (casters, priests or paladins). I found 3 lvl 55 elite priests, so i used shadow res aura and +12 stamina buff from food. Remember to use arcane torrent when the first mob is about to die in order to stop any healing in the area, then shield, heal yrself, start again, use a dense stone statue if you have it (thx jewelcrafting!), lay on hands, mana potion. Good luck, it's very hard.",
    "973511101531636772007/06/25 14:13:31LucifarkThanks for the nice Directions on how to get in there.\
\
Soloed at level 60 as a protection paladin, a few nice tips are as follows:\
\
1. Ensure to have a Major Mana Potion and a Heavy Runecloth Bandage.\
2. Keep Seal of wisdom on and Judgement of wisdom on your attack target at all times .\
3.Don't use arcane torrent immediately as suggested earlier but keep it to use once you've used some mana healing yourself.\
When you're almost oom and still getting beat use you lay on hands.\
\
You should be steadily regaining mana as they beat on you still and they should be oom (almost) now, with one dead.\
\
4. Use Divine Shield and Bandage yourself using the runecloth bandage.\
5. Keep up the steady healing and beating and watch as they die...\
\
Seal and judgement of wisdom is important though... use Mana tap as often as you can and use a second Arcane torrent if you can.\
\
Oh and even doing it as a 60 paladin i was ale to run out and only ahd to fight one of the mobs that guard the main door at teh entrance to the cathedral.\
\
Hope it all helps",
    "973536816201336372007/02/16 06:31:56LilyCan be soloed as a level 62 Retribution Paladin. Tyr's Hand is on the far southeastern corner of Eastern Plaguelands, and the Abbey is the small building on the left after you're through the front gate and running towards the fountain.\
\
You may need to die/revive until you're in the actual room (the wing on the left, ignore the stairs, doorway to your right), but once you are able to revive in the actual room (the Basin of Holy water is on a little plate on a desk in the room, and you can scout it out in ghost form and view which room actually has it) and I recommend hiding behind the bookcase at the entrance for a pre-fight buff/heal/eat/drink. \
\
Two Enchanters, one Cleric. Recommend bombarding the cleric with everything you have, from Consecration/Crusader Strike/Judgements etc, and interrupting heals with Hammer of Justice/Arcane Torrent/Repentance as necessary, and throwing on your Divine Shield and bandaging yourself as necessary. (I suggest Arcane Torrent first, to hit all 3 casters and interrupting any spells they are casting.)\
\
Throw on some Lay on Hands for good measure, and with luck and a good two-hander you should be able to finish off all three before they finish you off. \
\
Voila, basin is yours to loot. Recommend hearthing back out. Turn in your quest, buy your next quest items, and then it's pretty much just a trip to Scholomance, and combine with Crusader Aura for some wicked 220% Epic Mount Speed.",
    "973537197151336372007/02/16 19:12:14Lily- cough - \
