    "645193066101930662007/11/29 01:36:08ondreaThe corpse run idea is awesome. I was so tired of killing the same guys i decided to give it a try. Worked like a charm. Three lvl 41's in the crypt. I aggro'd 2 of them and killed them on the stairs and then went back for the other. As for getting out, I mounted up as soon as I was out of the crypt, rode to the bridge and jumped over it to the main path into Stromgarde. I made it out with 95% of my health still intact!\
Done as a solo 41 Ret Pally.... I was a little behind on my Arathi quests!\
:)",
    "645148142301481422007/09/02 13:42:36HansPrytzIf you, like me group, are too lazy to fight the same mobs again from the previous quest in the chain, here's a neat corpse run trick, that works especially well for this place.\
\
1) Have all party members buff up right before you engage the mobs. Damage absorbing spells are especially crucial.\
2) Run in! Keep running until you are across the bridge. If your party begins to run low on health mages should use frost nova and other classes instacast earthbinding abilities. (I'm playing a mage, so I don't know about any other classes skills)\
3) When you cross the bridge, turn left. When you die, make sure you do so with you corpse as close to the fence as possible! \
4) When you go to revive your corpse instead of turning left after the bridge, turn right and run around the house there, to the other side of the fence at which you died. \
5) Ress yourself and finish the quest. \
\
This may not be that much faster, but my group had been doing this long series of quest for 4 hours and we didn't want to kill the same mobs again. Also, instead of having to fight 25+ mobs, there are only 1-3 + the 3 defenders, which by the way can be solo pulled.\
\
Good luck!",
    "645210701102107012007/12/31 22:13:24LordshipTo take the prize, you have to get by [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npcs=7&filter=na=caretaker;ra=1;rh=-1;cr=6;crs=45;crv=0]these[/url] 3 lvl 41 cloth wearing melee guys. They can be pulled apart from one another and hove no special abilities except for running",
