    "7940159234501592342007/09/27 06:37:39TeacupYou can obtain either the Orb or Amulet of the Darkmoon by collecting tickets by handing in specific items. These items can range from [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=5134]Small Furry Paw[/url] to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=19933]Glowing Scorpid Blood[/url] as well as many crafted items by Blacksmiths, Engineers and Leatherworkers.\
\
[b]Note:[/b] In all of this, the auction house is your friend!\
\
You can gain a head start by solely handing in [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=5117]Vibrant Plumes[/url]. If you hand in other low level items you will gain less tickets and require more of an effort with the higher end - so don't do it! A total of [b]125[/b] [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=5117]Vibrant Plumes[/url] is required for [b]25[/b] turn ins (5 per turn in.) Giving you a total of 300 tickets.\
\
Now you require 900 more tickets. For maximum ticket gain, at 20 tickets per turn in, you have a choice of: 10 x [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=11404]Evil Bat Eyes[/url], 10 x [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=19933]Glowing Scorpid Blood[/url], 8 x [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=12644]Dense Grinding Stones[/url], 6 x [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=15994]Thorium Widgets[/url] or 8 x [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=15564]Rugged Armor Kit[/url].\
\
This equates to 45 turn ins, or depending on your choice of item:\
[ul]\
[li]450 [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=11404]Evil Bat Eyes[/url] (45 stacks.)[/li]\
[li]450 [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=19933]Glowing Scorpid Blood[/url] (45 stacks.)[/li]\
[li]1440 [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=12365]Dense Stone[/url] (72 stacks.)[/li]\
[li]810 [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=12359]Thorium Bar[/url] (40.5 stacks,) and 270 [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=14047]Runecloth[/url] (13.5 stacks.)[/li]\
[li]1800 [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=8170]Rugged Leather[/url] (90 stacks.)[/li]\
[/ul]\
\
Good luck! ^_^",
    "794083347083342006/12/07 09:13:17VanterTo get the 1200 tickets needed for this, you'll need to do 60 turnins at 20 tickets each.\
It depends greatly on your server's economy on which way is cheapest... Typically it's dense stone, but sometimes it's thorium bars.\
Here's a quick way to find out how much it's going to cost you per turnin:\
Multiply the cost of one stack (20) of each item by the number of stacks per turnin: 2 for rugged leather, 1.6 for dense stone, and for the widgets, .9 * Thorium Bars + .3 * Runecloth.\
Therefore, let's say that on your server, thorium bars cost 3g a stack, runecloth 1g, rugged leather 2g and dense stone 2g.\
That means each turn in costs 3g for thorium, 4g for leather, and 3.2g for stone. (for a total of 180g for 1200)\
Now you usually will end up using a combination, depending on what is on the AH at any given time, or your own farming skills, but this is a handy tool for those who plan on buying a majority of it.",
    "79401483412012006/10/05 08:30:34CreeestopherIt is definitely epic.  This has the most +dam/heal of any neck before outside of raids - and to get more +dam you need to run AQ ruins.  It's also got a good amount of +stam and +spi.  If it were just the stats or just the +dam, it'd be blue, but it's the combination of the two that makes it epic.",
