    "144615338npcAtal'ai Exile5598npcAtal'ai Exile55986550",
    "1446100244201002442007/06/07 14:31:34CatalyzeAs stated above, make sure to pull groups back into the unocuppied area because they can fear you. A Fear Ward on the tank or a PvP trinket that breaks fear will work well. Watch out for the spirit/ghost that will appear occassionaly. If possible, just move away from them (they float slowly around after certain mobs die). They hit hard and are a pain to kill. They will despawn in a few seconds so there is no need to fight them. Clear the room first and then attack the Boss.",
    "144614527110145272006/12/13 00:09:05SlarinWhen getting up to this guy watch out! The Undead fear you so make sure to stay back and have someone pull. If you get feared too close to the group, you'll tag the whole room.",
    "1446117227201172272007/07/08 01:27:51ThorandricPull groups one at a time into the room before the main chamber, get as far back as possible because some of the mobs can cast fear, and if u get feared and run into the main room you might agro a ton; the ghost that appear cannot be killed as they are immune to everything, and they will despwn after a few seconds but be sure to get away from them because they do indeed \"hit hard\" (it isnt that hard because they have an extremely slow movement speed)\
All in all the boss isnt that hard if your tank and healer is good",
    "1446186065501860652007/11/17 00:56:12Slybas11400 xp as of patch 2.3.",
    "1446126530201265302007/07/25 10:36:21rwstormbowI can't seem to find a good guide to this zone... after entering the instance the first left up leads to dragons. Which hall from the instance ent leads to Jammal ? thanks in advance for assistance... safe travels",
    "1446132401311002442007/08/05 01:48:08LinaeriThe Deathwalkers are the ones to move away from once they die since they will turn into a ghost for approximately 10-15 seconds which is immune to all damage but will disappear eventually.  They will randomly hit nearby members or the one who generates high threat (such as curing or taunting) and slowly chase them.  They also cast fear so it is highly important to have them pulled as far back as possible and other members must not run up or wait halfway to meet them, otherwise they may find themselves getting feared into the large room before they even engage the main tank.\
\
Corpse Eaters need to be stunned so that they do not consume any nearby corpses as they will regenerate most of their health if they eat.  Normal damage will only slow them down a little and will not stop them from eating.\
\
The High Priests nuke shadow bolts from a distance, summon non-elite skeletons, and can run away when low health so be sure to use earthbind totems, crippling poisons, or stun them before they go and fetch help.\
\
Jammal'an will sometimes use mind control on a random member, usually the main tank.  If you decide to take a boost with you for this battle don't be surprised if suddenly you find yourself being ganked by him once he/she's been MC'd.",
    "144658910120589102007/03/29 03:00:57djkeiththe quest ending is at Atal'al Exile (the quest giver) is at 33, 75 in hinterlands is what shinzo was meaning.",
    "14466496230649622007/04/10 11:17:57HarmbringerDifficult to get but a nice chunk of XP waiting at the end of the quest.",
    "1446120880201208802007/07/15 04:47:22NightdragonRemember to kill ALL the named trolls on the top floor first or the shield wont come down....it works best if ye do a little clean up first.  The mobs are not hard to kill if ye can get a group together in their 50's.....happy hunting!\
.",
    "1446131624411265302007/08/03 10:45:49VaidemineHere's your guide.  They have hi-res pictures, explanations, etc for the whole instance, as well as links if what you find isn't good enough for you...\
\
http://www.wowwiki.com/The_Temple_of_Atal%27Hakkar\
\
To answer your question, though, Jammal'an is on the same floor as the dragonkin, just in one of the chambers off to the side (south-east passage).  As Nightdragon mentioned, you'll need to kill all 6 of the named trolls on the top floor.  They are summoners that keep a force-field up in front of the room where Jammal'an is.  Once you take them down, you can enter the room and take him down.",
