    "5865297570529752007/03/18 02:34:29sandrockThe cave is at 44,44. Skirt the ruins along the right wall for easiest access to the cave. Hunters are found all over the ruins and there is a good concentration of Headhunters and Berserkers at 48,43.",
    "5861563960156392006/12/14 19:03:19chayaAna'thek is in a cave in the Ruins of Zul'Mamwe (lower level) with 2 adds. The Hunters are all around this level as well. On the upper level, by Mogh the Undying, you'll find the Berserkers and Headhunters, but only about 4 or 5 of each, so you'll need to wait for respawns.",
    "586209187102091872007/12/29 06:36:47ethersturmAs a level 44 rogue this was incredibly easy. For Ana'Thek, I sapped the caster and cheap shotted Ana'Thek, then straight away popped Blade Flurry. By the time Ana'thek was dead so was the melee bodyguard and then I just waited until my energy was back and killed the Caster.\
\
For the rest of the mobs I found its easier to pull them with a bow and then get behind a wall out of their LoS so that you can fight them one at a time, or in the case of a hunter, I liked to cheap shot the Hunter and blind his panther. Otherwise, its just as easy to sap the hunter and kill his panther first, but occasionally the hunter will resummon his pet half way through.",
    "586159444301594442007/09/27 14:32:17emero510Do  http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=209 and http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=598 at the same time. \
\
On my 44 warrior, this area is complete suck. everything runs, patrols all over, casters that don't pull easy, and respawn rates that'll make you /wrists. I've died so many times, I might as well be naked. \
\
Ana'thek was actually not that hard, just kill his healer if there is one first, and then run. Come back at full heath and take him out. He goes on little strolls around the area, but because of all the trash and pats, it's better to take him on in the cave.",
    "586197671101976712007/12/07 22:58:11DelendaSolo'd as a 41 hunter. Its not that hard, just make sure that you have the area cleared, wait until he comes all the way out of the cave, right before he turns around. send your pet in and right when it engages, put mend pet on. pop rapid fire and you're off to the races. \
it may be easier to have one of his two sidekicks attack you while the other stays on your pet, keeps your pet alive longer. \
\
anyways, that's just what I did",
    "5869151530915152007/05/27 04:24:05DevinI've soloed this as a 42 warlock. When Ana'thek is out of the cave, I got in and waited. Casted Howl of Terror to break the group apart and took him down easily. If you are an affliction warlock, they probably won't resist DoTs even with the level difference..",
    "5866114530611452007/04/02 15:21:25SqueeselfAna'thek occasionally wonders outside the cave with his entourage along the road. It's pretty easy to take him out and run from the adds while he's outside.",
    "586197047101970472007/12/06 17:20:38MeteorHawkVERY annoying quest to solo,especially as a Rogue.I was level 44 doing this quest and I died shortly after each kill.It is hugely irritating because:\
\
1.The mobs are very close together\
\
2.They run on low health and aggro the entire camp onto you\
\
3.WHEN you die,which you will do a lot,the graveyard is AAAAAAAAAL the way to the north.\
\
Tip:Bring a friend",
    "586198205101982052007/12/08 20:21:01ShadaxBe warned, the Skullsplitter Spirit chaser that may be with Ana'thek does a very ugly mana burn.  There's no doubt that they should be killed first.",
    "586205605102056052007/12/22 13:48:39FrumpySoloed Ana'Thek and his adds as a 43 druid, used one healing potion but probably could have done it without it.\
\
1. Start in cat form prowled and pounce Ana'thek.  Burst him down as quick as possible and watch the mystic, if he starts to heal pop in bear form and feral charge.\
\
2. Once you get him down pop out to caster form, War Stomp, Regrowth, (use potion if you have one), and pop into bear form.\
\
3. Start hitting the mystic and use Frenzied Regeneration.\
\
4. Just maul both of them down.",
  },
