    "45017243821441732007/04/25 01:57:55SplasWhile you are at it, do this quest too: http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=3882\
They drop from the Diemetradon's as well as the scales",
    "45016276221441732007/04/05 21:24:20SumitaI found a good group of Pterrordaxs at 43.87 and the Frenzied ones at 25.39. Doing this with the Shizzle's Flyer quest, both these drop the webbed things you need for that quest as well.",
    "45018154530815452007/05/11 17:53:39deadalone57,86 is another spot for regular Pterrordax's",
    "45014024110402412007/02/22 00:13:47vexis58Soloed this quest with some difficulty as a level 51 warrior. The main danger with the Frenzied Pterrodaxes (found mainly to the western side of the volcano, north of Terror Run) is that they tend to be near other mobs that aggro -- other pterrodaxes and diemetradons especially. I died several times from aggro. The diemetradons have a harsh strength/agility debuff, which was extremely bad for me as a warrior. Also be careful to watch for Devilsaurs, since several patrol the area as well.\
\
The regular Pterrodaxes can easily be found in the area near the northern pylon (http://www.wowhead.com/?object=164955) but there are not enough there to complete the quest. If you kill off every pterrodax there, you will find about 5 or 6 of them. It's helpful to kill half of what you need the first time, then come back on your way back to turn in quests and get the other half.",
    "45015211441441732007/03/16 12:12:08rgummerI ran around for an hour trying to find Pterrordaxs in the crater, but could only find three.  Finally, I found a bunch of them south of the slithering scar up in the mountains.  The coordinates are (44.5, 90.1) with the wowhead client.  The path up to it starts at (46.3, 86.4)",
    "450115238541159122007/09/13 07:06:17bEwaReI think you mean 51-53 lvl range",
    "450115912180159122006/12/15 14:40:44BadfishMy suggestion, first complete Crystals of Power (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=4284).  Then pick up the unlocked quests, Western Crystal Pylon, Northern Pylon, and Eastern Pylon.  Now head over to the Northern Pylon @ http://www.wowhead.com/?object=164955, that same area is where you will find your 10 Pterrodax.  Now once you've finished there, head over to the Eastern Pylon @ http://www.wowhead.com/?object=164957.  Continue on towards the Western Pylon @ http://www.wowhead.com/?object=164956.  (Side note: I suggest you cut through The Marshlands with all the Ravasaurs for time, but once you hit the Slithering Scar stick to the wall of Un'goro until you reach the Western Pylon, you'll find a few Frenzied Pterro's along the way.).  Much like the Northern Pylon you'll find that the same hill which has the Western Pylon is a wonderful spot to kill most of the 15 Frenzied Pterrodax required by the quest.  Their levels range from 31-33 and you don't have to worry about large roaming elites.  There you go, knocked out 4 quests :].\
Edit:  Watch out, Pterrodax fear.",
    "450119655411815452007/12/05 16:28:27GotmarkConfirmed. A good spot with 5-7 Pterrodax's and not a lot of people are there.",
  },
  ["In Eranikus' Own Words55"] = {
    "351215548npcItharius5353npcUmbranse the Spiritspeaker85884200",
    "351216386110163862006/12/16 21:34:58glassthorneFirstly, one can disregard the \"Progress\" section of this article.  This refers to a questline from Un'Goro Crater and not the Essence of Eranikus.\
\
Secondly, this quest chain seems to be an incomplete one. \
\
After you turn in the Chained Essence of Eranikus to Itharius and go to visit Umbranse, the chain dead ends with its completion.  He will not point you to another questgiver or give you any task to complete.  Though it would seem that what he says would, logically, lead to another part, it does not, which is a disappointment.\
\
Messages to the GMs and on the forums have yielded nothing except messages that the quest is \"working as intended\".",
    "35125296961192832007/03/18 02:09:35DeeBeeIt would be interesting to know, considering the previous glassthorne's commment of \"Working as intended\", if the quest line isn't actually broken, just incomplete.\
\
There is a difference, after all. One means bugfixes. The other means a more creative and complex solution is required, which may take more time to do.",
    "351217389821163862007/10/23 18:27:53TyrsenusThis quest line will likely never be finished.  In the Ahn'Quiraj scepter quest line, the player redeems [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=15491]Eranikus[/url], effectively making the intent of this quest line obsolete.  One should note that his stolen \"potent augury device\" was likely his book taken by the Argent Dawn, as it shows up in a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=6030]quest[/url] that starts in Everlook.",
    "35125726761192832007/03/26 01:13:18SyllvosIt isn't neccesarily broken, it is indeed \"Working As Intended.\" However, in this case, working as intended is the end. Eranikus cannot be redeemed via any spirit speaker, the quest is continued in the green scepter shard quest- Tyrande and Remulous redeem him while moonglade is under attack, he then gives you the green scepter shard.",
    "351219283110192832007/01/04 06:46:29DeckerI spoke with a GM today (04-01-2007) and he confirmed that this quest is indeed broken and will be fixed sometime in the furture.",
    "3512142648201426482007/08/23 04:31:28AvoozlUmbranse is standing in a shack in in Winterspring at 68,27, east of Mon Horror Den.\
Chal Fairwind, lvl 53 Night Elf, stands just outside the shack and is hostile to Horde but won't attack unless you attack first.\
