    "8153204512102045122007/12/20 14:38:55marshtompereThe drop rate is like 6% but u have 2 kill like 100 of them just 2 get 2!!!",
    "81536628640662862007/04/12 20:58:54JohnJSalI found a lot of them at 62,18, and no hippogryphs around either.",
    "8153194829101948292007/12/02 10:24:28distomosJust to the south of the Legash Encampment, you can find a wide source of Mosshoofs. However, you will also find a lot of Thunderhead Skystormers. However, I can confirm that if you kill Thunderhead Skystormers, more Mosshoofs will spawn. They are fairly easy to kill, too -- I'm level 50 and not having a problem.",
    "8153121474211052062007/07/16 07:19:46redandgrayHonestly, it does not matter one bit how you take them. Do not listen to the silly superstitious commentors. A kill is a kill. Period. My cat ripped into 10 of them and I got my two \"perfect\" antlers, no prob. The biggest time sink was finding them and plowing through the swarms of hippogryphs along the way.\
\
Took me a lot longer to collect the 6 Wavethrasher scales in the next segment of the chain.",
    "815393531093532006/12/07 18:54:31DuelicionThe antlers are indeed a very low drop rate but there are about 3 different places to find them. So if you are having problems with the drop rate I suggest moving to a different place and starting to look there. Also don't let the drop rate discourage you from the quest becuase the trinket you can get is an amazing help for any hunter. I am talking about the devilsaur eye. I still use it on my 60 hunter. It helps and after the antlers isn't to hard to get.",
    "8153175711017572006/10/11 08:22:57SidewalkThe Mosshoof Coursers who drop these, are in the northern and southern region of Azshara. Basically just run north from where Ogtinc gives you the quest.",
    "815393151093152006/12/07 18:43:13blackironFor this and the Wave Trasher quest after, go for the higher level mobs.  In the case of these, the coursers, focus exclusively on the level 53 coursers.  The levels of the coursers are not evenly dispersed.  The stretch extending northwest from the blue dragons contains primarily level 52 coursers.  You find more concentrated level 53 coursers by heading east or northeast, but watch out for the giants.  It will still take a long time, but more like 30 minutes instead of two hours.",
    "8153194830101948302007/12/02 10:26:55distomosAlso, be sure to have Beast Tracking up. With the 2.3 changes, they will now show as a yellow dot on your screen among the several red.",
    "8153188638101886382007/11/21 00:35:50amiga2091Killed six and finished! First one and sixth one dropped the perfect antlers. Coords were 36,70",
    "8153197791101977912007/12/08 04:12:26DayruinerTerrible odds getting any for me, but them being skinnable and all, I got made a killing in AH selling their leather, and leveled to 55 in the process. I'd do the quest when you are nice and rested, more exp that way, just good for the frustration this  quest generates, btw, for me, It took about 50 of them then I got both of them consecutively...",
    "81531722410172242006/12/19 05:54:36Odonthe1stI've seen widely differing opinions about this quest.  And for my self and the 1 hunter I helped, a big difference in how it played out.  I killed nearly 100 mosshoof coursers to get the 2 perfect antlers, lucky for me I skin.  2 days later I helped a friend and he got 2 with 8 kills.  So just be patient and make sure you're killing the right coursers, there are others coursers besides the mosshoof in the area.",
    "8153165536101655362007/10/10 10:24:25PizzaManThere are lots of coursers in the area between the Legash Encampment (satyr camp) and Thalassian Base Camp (blood elves).\
\
Be prepared to kill for a while. I finally got the first antler on the 29th kill and the second one four kills later.",
    "8153163804201638042007/10/06 14:45:27inmediasresI recommend route between points (35,62) and (42,72). Until you make one run, you can turn back, as they have respawned",
