Make sure you have your Vitrous Focuser in the bag, if you dont have one you can buy it from the AD Alchemist in Chillwind Camp. Also remember to equip your AD Commendation trinket (Save all your scourgestones for when you hit revered).\
\
If you are 60 the best place to go grind  is The Ruins of Andorhal, I can get about 100 Osseous Agitators and 3 stacks of Runecloth in an hour worth of grinding as a Rogue, if you are a caster it may be a bit less due to downtime. For a lower level your best bet is going to Felstone Field itself. (Always remember that the trick of grinding is killing mobs that you can finish off in 20 seconds or less and that respawn fast). \
\
When you have a good amount of Runecloth and Osseous Agitators head to Chillwind Camp and buy some Arcane Quickener from the AD Alchemist (Those are expensive and if you dont use them fast they will despawn from your bags, so only buy what you need). Return to Felstone Field and use the cauldron to deliver the quest. \
\
Then Rinse and repeat. Each turn in will give you about 15 rep for non-humans and about 17 rep for humans.",
