    "42442707820270782007/01/29 11:06:18NovaheartYou need a Mithril casing [http://www.wowhead.com/?item=10561] to go on to the Final part of the quest [http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=4245]  which are made by 215 engineers.",
    "424416937741652532007/10/15 22:13:16SavvycatI would not \"be very careful\" about buying a Mithril Casing. Regardless of the fact that gold in Outland is vastly more plentiful, even by old world standards, the price of a Mithril Casing is low. Take this from someone who has farmed for their epic flying mount, and has always had enough gold for the prior mounts. Upon levelling up my 2nd character on a different server, I have a different perspective to gold in this game, and in my opinion, losing 40 silver or even more, is well worth it to gain 3950 exp at this level, considering it will help me get to Outland faster.",
    "42446525340652532007/04/10 23:38:53MaxtroBe very careful if you decide to buy a Mithril Casing. The reward for finishing the quest line is only 1g 60s and XP. If Mithril Casing's are selling for a over 2g buy the mats Mithril Ore or Bars and ask an Eng to make it for you.",
    "424416664741652532007/10/12 12:37:24jcook264The important thing to weigh out is not only the price, but the XP. If completing the mission gets you your level than to me its worth it.",
    "424419689311652532007/12/06 11:06:35Athakayou can earn like 5G at lvl 50-55 in the meantime u search for a engineer, so buy it of AH is the (BY FAR) best thing to do. considering 1G = 1K xp (@ lvl 70). so u get @ 15K xp now for the q's u get of it. thats 15G worth of XP.. 100% worth it",
    "424317651331785002007/10/29 17:48:56DiiCEThis area is full of it... more Nintendo references: NPC's Linken, Larion and Muigin, all in Marshal's Refuge.",
    "424319117011785002007/11/25 18:07:09SilverniaLet's not forget the Fraggle Rock references.  hehe  ^_~   NPC \"Spraggle Frock\" and area \"Fungal Rock\".\
\
-S",
    "424365684230656842007/04/11 18:26:16scoopThat helped heaps, Thank you.\
