    "1381178214201782142007/11/02 16:18:15PlaguebearerTook it as a level 40 hunter, died once.\
\
The first two waves are easy, but it would have gone a lot faster with some more thought. MAKE SURE YOUR PET ATTACKS BEFORE YOUR TRAPS GO OFF.\
\
First Wave: Place a freezing trap and kill whichever doesn't get frozen. Fire a single shot at the second one, then allow your pet to kill it while you regain mana. sometime before it dies, throw down another trap and heal your pet.\
\
Second Wave: After your first trap goes off, lay another one. Kill whichever centaur isn't frozen. If the advisor becomes unfrozen at any time, make sure to focus fire them. Just pick them off as best you can. Don't bother with the freezing trap while you kill the last one, as the third wave will stop at the bottom of the ramp to the horn and walk up slowly.\
\
Third Wave: Place a trap when you see the third wave coming up. You should get the Khan. Attack the advisor first. Activate Rapid Fire and burn down  your pets targets as fast as possible, and keep healing up on your pet throughout. If you can, attempt to move the fight towards the bottom of the ramp. If the Khan becomes free, freeze him again. If your pet dies at any time, feign death, rez your pet, and try again. Once all three escorts are dead, bring the Khan to the horn. Take your pet's growl off, and if your pet has hate, dps until he targets you. Now, lay a frost trap next to the horn. This is the fun part. Now you just continue kiting the Khan in circles around the horn until he's dead.\
\
That's my guide for hunters, I'll try and update as I level my other characters.",
