\
On the second wave (three mobs), distract one near the base of the ramp, and the other two will continue walking. Sap one and kill the other once they are out of range of the distracted mob. If the distracted one continues up the ramp after distract wears off, kill him and then the sapped one. Sometimes though, it will stop at the ramp, and you can kill the sapped one first.\
\
On the third wave (three mobs and the elite), ideally distract the three non-elite mobs and take out the elite with a lot of stuns. If you do this, bring the elite up near the horn, because the pack of three will usually stop a little bit before the horn after distract wears off. You still have sap and blind if some mobs get through.\
\
