    "2873124667101246672007/07/21 19:21:03borbesHere's what I did. As mentioned above there are 4 quests to completed here. I completed Southsea Shakedown and Pirate Hats Ahoy! first. \
\
Andre Firebeard requires a 4 pull though. I cleared all the single pulls around him them pulled his group towards the house for Stoley's Shipment. I killed and looted Firebeard then shortly after died to the rest of his group. Then when I came back, I res'd inside the house where the shipment is, got it, then hearthed out.",
    "2873129511601295112007/07/31 00:00:35VortixPirate camp is located at 72,45 or at the easternmost point of land directly east of the caverns of time.",
    "287358774140587742007/03/28 19:14:38ChalkdustFun little trick to complete this way under-level: run into the pirate camp and make a beeline for the two-story house to the right.  If you can get close enough, and get killed, take your ghost upstairs to the bedroom and you can usually resurrect inside, loot the cargo and hearth (or, since I was on my shaman, Astral Recall) to safety.",
    "2873267319026732006/11/03 13:23:36BenoitXVIThe shipment is in the house to the right of the camp on the second floor but watch out as there is like 4-5 pirates just down the stairs that lead to the second floor and they can't be pulled one by one.",
    "2873208726202087262007/12/28 11:49:55KuzazieYou get \"Stoley's Shipment\" from Stoley in Steamwheedle Port, but before you set off to get Stoley's Shipment, it may be a good idea to get these quests:  WANTED: Andre Firebeard (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=2875), Southsea Shakedown (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=8366), and\
Pirate Hats Ahoy! (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=8365), because you have to go to the same place for all of them. There's really no need to worry about the trip just South of Steamwheedle Port to Lost Rigger Cove, because the shore's just lined with neutral 41-44 tortoise until you get closer to Lost Rigger Cove, where you run into some of the Pirates. Being a 48 druid, it was really easy to just prowl past everything until I got to the first 2-story building on my right after I went past the little arch thing that leads to the main part of Lost Ringer Cove. When you first walk in, there's 3 pirates, and for me, their levels were 44, 45, and another 44 (but it probably varies). It's a good idea to kill the 3 bobos here. Then, you walk up a small staircase, and there's 3 more pirates, levels of 45, 45, and 44 for me. If you try to pull them one at a time here, they'll all aggro, so be ready for combat! I tried prowling past, but I aggroed. Then there's a larger double staircase, and taking that, you get to the second story, where the Stoley's Shipment is (on the left wall for me). It's a little obvious----it glows like when your computer's telling you that you can loot something (there's like 4 or 5 stacks of Stoley's Shipment, but you can only take one). Pretty easy for level 48, but good luck!! ^_^",
    "287319082400190822007/01/02 09:41:53WildWBe sure to do all theese quests at the same time;\
\
