    "8425106112101061122007/06/17 16:52:38BinoPrimeOk, I need some serius help here! I'm a Fury Warior and the + hit rating in the shoulders is pretty good for me but still replaceable. I wonder how easy it is to find better trinket / shoulders in the rest of the game. (This is my main and i dont know enything about the rest of WoW)",
    "8425136711013672006/10/02 14:57:54gotlerThe Diamond Flask seems to be the way to go, since the two other rewards are replaceable. And even though the Flask has a long cooldown, the duration of it still makes you able to keep the effect up for 10% of the time, which is about the average for such trinkets.",
    "8425100476601004762007/06/08 01:02:59gazkwJust remembering the reward choice when I was presented with the 3 items. All of them are very nice rewards.\
\
Based on comments from various sources I chose the Diamond Flask. Needless to say, I regretted that choice. I was a Fury warrior and shoulders with +hit are very rare. I only managed to get nice +hit shoulders with the Epic lvl 60 pvp shoulders.\
\
Diamond Flask is ok, but you will definitely find better dps trinkets along the way to 60. IMO, the shoulders are pricless. I even wanted to have a GM change them for me once, but decided not to, as there was limited item restore for characters.\
\
Fury Visor is nice, but as I had Lionheart Helm, there was no question.\
\
I strongly recommend the Razorsteel Shoulders, esp if you are a Fury warrior.",
    "8425148234101482342007/09/02 17:02:15KainyPick whichever is the largest upgrade to your current equipment.\
