    "2768614714061472006/12/05 12:29:06FiranTo start the quest event you have to kill the Sandfury Executioner at the top of the Temple and use the key he drops to free Sergeant Bly from his cage. \
\
After freeing Bly several waves of level 42-45 trolls spawn at the bottom of the steps (some but not all elite). It is best to wait at the top of the steps and kill each wave of spawns as they come to you, because if you go down the steps you may agro additional trolls. If you toggle pvp on you will get heals from the orc npc priest, but they won't usually save you from dying. After fighting several waves of trolls Bly leads you down the steps and you fight the two bosses. Neither are particularly difficult, though you do fight both at once so make sure to off-tank one of them. \
\
Once the bosses are killed you can talk to the goblin who will blow up the gates to Chief Ukorz Sandscalp. Do not talk to Bly until everybody is ready, because doing so causes Bly and his group to agro and attack you. Kill off the priest and lock first, then the rogue and finally Bly himself. Loot his body for the divino-matic rod and the quest is complete. \
\
To do this quest your group needs to be slightly higher than it does for most of the instance. Most of the members should be around level 50. Good healing and Dps is probably more important on this encounter than healing.",
    "27682588290258822007/01/27 17:43:07djallowayThere is an easy way to take out Bly and his crew after you've finished off all the spawns.\
(after you have the Demolition guy blow up the door to the last boss that is)\
Wait for them to begin to Hearthstone (yes if you wait long enough Bly and his gang will begin to hearth away).\
Then talk to Bly at the last second and his teammates will continue to hearth and leave.... leaving only Bly to kill.",
    "276812749251258822007/07/27 01:54:21ZsarinaCan confirm this does work. As all of them start hearthing, talk to Bly, he will appear to keep hearthing but he stayed behind while all the others will leave.\
