    "92481252630125262006/12/10 01:10:29BinaryWhile this quest may seem unnecessarily hard, the reward from it (in terms of both item and faction) can be considered worth it.\
\
To complete this quest, simply collect 12 Abyssal Crest for a Mrdallion of Station, and then 3 Abyssal Signets for a Ring of Lordship.\
From there, you can summon the boss that you must kill to pick up the Abyssal Scepter.\
Note that the boss requires at least 20 decent-geared players to be downed.\
\
The ring is blue and provides nice NR for the various dungeons that utilize nature damage.\
However, you might just want to pick up a Jasper Link of Nature Resistance (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=11978) off the AH for an amount of gold depending on your server.\
\
In addition to the ring, you also recieve 200 reputation.",
    "924810872321125262007/06/21 14:23:34maximusprimeSince TBC came out, everyone goes to Outland at 58.  This quest was designed pre-TBC for level 60 players who could no longer gain experience.  I assume that Blizzard knows this, as well as the fact that Silithus is rarely visited nowdays (as are the old 60 dungeons/raids like Onyx, Naxx, Strat, Scholo, AQ20/40, ZG, BWL, and MC).  \
\
The point is that there is no real reason to do this quest now that you can go to Outland and get better gear (and 10 levels).  So, don't worry about it.",
    "92486269311125262007/04/05 18:16:05maldianThis quest was designed to be completed by a large group of level 60 players back when the level cap had been 60 for quite some while.  It does seem a little weird, but if there isn't one, I guess they just decided an XP reward was superfluous.",
