    "78493241610324162007/02/07 20:09:42hobowillreturnsSolo-able by a talented Rogue or Druid (I was 48).\
\
To get the skull; I Hibernated one wolf, and rooted the other. Ran away until I lost aggro (if you run parallel to the path, uphill-side, there are no trolls for about 100ft, so you may lose aggro and re-stealth).\
\
The bones were much harder, as you can neither hibernate nor root the Oozes. I just had to solo the elites face-on. Barkskin, the Defilers Talisman and War Stomp are all great if you have them; feral druids and rogues will stand a better chance toe-to-toe without them than Balance.",
    "7849186070401860702007/11/17 01:03:58catspats31As of patch 2.3, the Vilebranch Raiding Wolves and the Jade Sludges are no longer elite, therefore this is no longer a group quest. It also gives away 6800 XP if you complete this quest.",
    "7849402520040252006/11/22 23:05:36OrmrissThe skull is found in a Pile of Skulls, which is in a small walled-in area at the very top of Jintha'alor.  As soon as you get to the top level, head to the right.  There is a walled area with trolls, and further to the right is another area with wolves.  That's where you'll find the skull.\
\
The bones are in a Pile of Bones near the slimes/oozes.  This is on the level right before the top.  The area you are looking for is right next to the stairs that connect this level to the one below it.  You should be able to see the oozes moving around, as well as a wall of wooden spikes.  The spikes surround a pit/depressed area, and the bones are in the middle.  You will need to kill about seven elite oozes to reach them.  Just pick one side and kill your way around.\
\
Quest is worth it since it is relatively easy and stacks with several other quests out of Revantusk Village.  Plus, if you can't use either quest reward, take the legplates and sell them.  Combined with the quest's monetary reward, you'll come away a little more than 3g richer.",
