The giant was also a pain, spent about 2 hours looking for one. Eventually, I gave up and decided to do some fishing off Satheriss Strand, and he appeared right on top of me! Got the tumour first time. \
\
For those of you hunting the giant, I suggest go down to the Strand and wait there. Kill some of those pesky Nagas or go fishing to pass the time. Eventually a giant will spawn there - I think it must be the start of his path, and/or the spawn is triggered, so it seems like the best place to pick one up.",
    "1383187982301879822007/11/19 23:03:03SistaroseI found the quest was easy, no need to leave the swamp, the Green Whelp Blood was picked up at Itharius's Cave(13,59) from the Dreaming Whelp. Just head south after getting the fungus.",
    "13831017340101732006/12/07 23:24:40dreampodPretty simple quest.\
\
The Mire Lord fungus and Shadow Panther hearts are easy drops off of regular mobs in the Swamp of Sorrows.  The Mire Lord is located in the cave at the North Western end of Misty Valley (coordinates 5,31).  The Panther's can be found along the edge of the Shadowmurk and the Misty Reed Strand, they are stealthed however so they may be difficult to find without something to boost your detection.\
\
The Deepstrider Tumor can be gotten off of the Elite Giants in Desolace.  They aren't too difficult and the most reliable place to find the is in the ocean just south of Ethel Rethor, near the Drysnap Crawlers.  Easy to combo this part of the quest with hunting for the keys.\
\
Turn it in for some amusing dialogue, then deliver the poison to Stonard for some easy XP.",
